title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out dough. Layer pepperoni and cheese.
Roll dough back up.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Beat egg with a little water. Brush top of dough with egg.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Slice to serve.

title: unbelievable chicken
directions: Put chicken in Dutch oven, heavy pot or electric skillet. Pour on ketchup. (Do not salt and pepper.) Pour Pepsi-Cola over chicken. Let simmer on low heat on top of stove about 30 minutes covered. Take lid off; turn chicken over and simmer on low heat another 30 minutes uncovered. Then serve it. More Pepsi or water can be added, if needed.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Boil the chopped dates, sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Roll dough as for jelly roll. Spread with date mixture.
Roll up.
Place in refrigerator until firm enough to slice. Bake until lightly brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy peanut patty candy
directions: In heavy 3-quart saucepan mix sugar, water and Karo together and bring to a boil.
Add peanuts and food coloring.
Cook, stirring often, until mixture forms a firm ball when a little is dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo, salt and vanilla.
Beat mixture until it loses its gloss and begins to hold shape when dropped from a spoon.
(Do not overbeat as mixture sets rapidly.)
Pour at once onto a large greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into small pieces.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Fold in mashed bananas, vanilla and mayonnaise.
Stir in chopped nuts. Grease and flour 1 Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Do not use pans coated with a nonstick surface (Teflon).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or when toothpick comes out clean.
You can use powdered sugar glaze when cake cools.

title: kimberly's milkshake
directions: Put in blender and blend well.

title: so you forgot to defrost chicken
directions: Place frozen chicken in slow cooker.
Mix together soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper and pour over chicken.
Cover.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: marinated oriental chicken
directions: Marinate chicken a day ahead.
Combine first 7 ingredients in large shallow dish.
Add chicken to marinade.
Cover with plastic and refrigerate 1 hour or overnight, turning occasionally. Preheat broiler.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Broil chicken until brown and cooked through, about 5 minutes per side. Sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Servings: 4.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients
and cook in a large covered pot until vegetables are cooked done.
Then add small pieces of your favorite pot pie or dumpling recipes to the soup mixture and cook in the pot, uncovered, until they are done.
When dumplings have cooked through, add a pinch of soda and 1 pint of milk to the mixture.
Bring to a boil.

title: coconut-buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: easy eggplant mozzarella
directions: Brown beef, onions, celery or green pepper.
Drain off fat. Add liquids.
Add thinly sliced eggplant and simmer uncovered in skillet 15 minutes or until eggplant is tender.
Add cheese to top and simmer until melted.
Serve plain or over noodles.
This mixture is even better as a leftover placed inside a pita pocket. Add more cheese to the top and melt in oven.

title: baked cheesecake pie
directions: Combine
cream	cheese,
1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and salt in bowl; mixing well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time,
mixing well after each addition.
Pour into pie shell. Bake on baking sheet at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set. Combine sour
cream,
tablespoons
sugar
and
1/4 teaspoon vanilla in bowl.
Spread over pie.
Bake for 10 minutes longer; cool.	Chill until firm.
Garnish with fruit.

title: jello cake
directions: Cook cake. Mix by directions on package.
Let cool.
Put holes in cake about 1 1/2-inches apart. Make holes about the size of a small pencil.
Make jello and pour evenly over top of cake. Put in fridge for an hour or two, then cover with Cool Whip.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil cocoa, butter, sugar and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Add oatmeal, coconut, chopped nuts and drop onto waxed paper.

title: banana-peach shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend about 30 seconds or until smooth.
Serve immediately over ice cubes. Low-fat and low-cholesterol.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together. Make into a ball and roll into chopped nuts.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix together and use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of water.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla while beating. Gradually add sugar. Beat until stiff peaks form. Fold in chocolate chips and pecans. Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn off heat. Leave in oven until oven is completely cool.

title: swedish dilled meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, ground pork, bread crumbs, egg, onion, milk, dill, 2 teaspoons salt, Worcestershire sauce and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: candy cookies squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and water until blended.
Pat into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes.
Layer marshmallows, M&M's candies, peanut morsels and pecans.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes or until marshmallows begin to melt. Cut into squares.
Yields 24 squares.

title: dirt and worm cake
directions: You will also need a new flower pot and a spade to serve with.

title: uncooked marshmallow cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler. Then add remainder of mixture.
Roll in desiccated coconut or walnuts (crushed).
Form in a long roll.
Store in refrigerator and slice cold.

title: posh squash
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender.
Drain thoroughly and drain again, cool slightly.
To beaten eggs add mayonnaise, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Stir squash in gently.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and melted margarine and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Makes 5 servings.

title: turkey supper dressing
directions: Boil turkey parts in 6 cups of water until tender.
Break bread into cubes.
Moisten bread with juice.
Add sage, onion, salt and beaten eggs.
Mix, kneading, until all is moist and blended, making dressing soft.
Add ground meat.
Mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 20.

title: cornbread dressing(health conscious)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, boil the water. Add celery and onion; cook for 2 to 3 minutes, or until soft.
In a medium bowl, toss cornbread crumbs, bread cubes, sage, parsley and poultry seasoning to mix well.
Add chicken stock and egg white; mix again.
Pour the celery, onion and cooking liquid into the bowl; mix well.
Spray a 2-quart casserole with vegetable oil spray.
Pour mixture in, dot with margarine and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: budget low-fat turkey divan
directions: In a bowl, place turkey, egg white, mustard, thyme and pepper. Combine until well blended.
Form mixture into 4 to 6 patties.

title: christmas pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in hash browns, cheese, milk, onions and seasoning.
Pour into 9 inch pie tin.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Save 1 Tbsp. of fat.
Crumble bacon over egg mixture. Combine cornflakes and bacon fat.
Sprinkle over egg mixture. Cover and refrigerate over night.
Bake uncovered at 325 degrees for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pepper relish
directions: Cover peppers and onion with boiling water and let set 10 minutes. Drain; cover with boiling water and bring to a boil.
Let stand 10 minutes. Drain. Mix ingredients and cook 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal. May process in canner 5 minutes.

title: grandma's popcorn balls
directions: Melt marshmallows with margarine over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Pour over combined corn and gumdrops.
Toss until well coated.
Moisten hands with butter or warm water; form into balls. They are very pretty and delicious.

title: glazed molasses cake
directions: Stir soda into sour milk or cream.
Add to creamed lard and sugar.
Add eggs to the first ingredients.
Add molasses and beat well.
Sift flour, cinnamon and ginger together into first mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coffee cake(portuguese)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour half the batter in a greased and floured angel cake pan.
Add half the cinnamon mix.
Pour remaining batter over the cinnamon mix.
Add remaining cinnamon mix on top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Line dish with raw hamburger mixed with salt and pepper to taste and onion.
Add green beans.
Pour mushroom soup over all. Do not dilute.
Spread slivers of cheese over this and cover top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours or more and until beans are cooked.

title: hot seafood dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave cream cheese 2 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients, except seafood.
Mix well.
Add seafood and microwave 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: my brother's favorite chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Beat together mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Sift flour, sugar and cocoa together; add to mayonnaise mixture.
Grease and flour pan (layer pans, tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan can be used). Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: doritos and soup casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Put a layer of browned meat, then a layer of Doritos in casserole dish.
Repeat process until all is gone.
Pour mixture of soups, taco sauce and green chilies over last layer.
Top with crumbled Doritos and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: glenn's favorite dessert
directions: In a 9 X 13 inch baking pan, put pie filling in the bottom. Add the cake mix evenly over the pie filling.
Slightly press the nuts and coconuts into the cake mix.
Drizzle the butter evenly over all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325 degrees for one hour.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Combine orange rind, juice and egg; add to dry ingredients, just enough to moisten. Fold in cranberries.
Turn into greased and floured loaf pan; bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over drained fruit.
Let set 30 minutes. Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and dash of pepper.
Add chicken broth and cream or milk.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
If desired, garnish with snipped parsley.
Makes 3 main-dish servings.

title: oatmeal chippers
directions: Beat together shortening, vanilla and sugar until creamy. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture egg and milk. Mix until thoroughly blended.
Stir in oats, nuts and chocolate pieces.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: summer berry pie
directions: Mix berries in large bowl.
Pour into pastry shell.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over berries in pastry shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Top pie with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: mulligan soup
directions: In a large soup pot, start 1 quart of water to boil.
Cut beef into bite size pieces.
Add to water along with bouillon.
Chopped carrots, potatoes and celery are added next.
Add tomatoes and cabbage.
Stir in spices to taste.
About 20 minutes before finished, add lima beans, green beans and corn.
Cook until meat and veggies are tender.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Stir occasionally and add water if needed.

title: bean week pie
directions: Brown the ground beef, adding onions.
Drain and mix with beans.
Prepare cornbread mix according to directions on the package.
In a well-greased pie plate, layer the meat and bean mixture alternately with the cornbread mixture.
Top with cornbread mix.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Moisten plain gelatin with cold water.

Add sugar to pumpkin, milk, spices and egg yolk. Cook in double boiler until thick. Add moistened gelatin to pumpkin and mix well. Cool; when thickened slightly fold in sugar and stiff egg whites. Pour into baked pie shell. Chill. Serve with whipped cream.

title: frozen cherry dessert
directions: Mix together and freeze in large, flat dish covered with foil. Take from freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: western chili
directions: Combine all 6 cans and simmer in a 4-quart boiler or cook in a crock-pot on low for 4 hours.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes, leave skins on, cut into cubes and toss with sliced onions and spices.
Turn onto Reynolds Wrap, add 3 big pats of butter, cover with foil and place on grill or into oven at 350 degrees until soft.

title: pork and bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add tomato soup and pork and beans; stir well, then add chili powder.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1 cup cheese; place biscuits (I flatten the biscuits with my hand).
Place remaining cheese on biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are brown.
Yields 5 (1-cup) servings.

title: dorene watts' scalloped cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage; boil for 8 minutes.
Drain and place in baking dish with alternate layers of cheese.
Add White Sauce.
Cover top with crumbs sauteed in butter.
Bake until crumbs are brown in hot oven (450°).

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage. Add onions and cook until soft. Add seasoning salt and garlic powder.
Add dirty rice mix and water.
Cook until liquid is gone over low heat.

title: calico bean hot pot
directions: Brown bacon, beef and onion.
Drain and add beans.
Combine catsup, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and salt.
Mix with bean mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until hot through.

title: hamburger noodle stroganoff
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles and drain.
Melt margarine in skillet; saute onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Add beef and cook until browned.
Remove from heat; stir in flour, tomato sauce, wine, beef broth, salt and pepper.
Return to heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in sour cream; do not boil. Layer meat mixture with noodles in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.

title: honey spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add garlic, Italian seasoning and wine.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over vermicelli.
tags: chunky garden style spaghetti sauce with mushrooms

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook cocoa, flour, sugar, milk and egg yolks in double boiler until very thick, then add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use egg whites or Cool Whip for topping.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Put crescent rolls in a jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool. Combine dressing, mayonnaise and cream cheese. Spread on crescent rolls.
Add favorite vegetables and shredded cheese.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: linguine with chicken livers(this is easy, unusual, inexpensive and delicious.)
directions: Saute onions and bacon in oil until soft.
Add salt, pepper and tomatoes, breaking up whole tomatoes with a wooden spoon as they simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in the red pepper.
Continue cooking until sauce is thickened and has body and flavor (perhaps 1/2 hour, this is not a 3 hour number).

title: divine divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and coffee in saucepan.
Place over low heat and boil until mixture forms threads when dropped from a spoon (230° to 234° on candy thermometer).
Slowly pour half the syrup into egg whites, beating while pouring.

title: tannies
directions: Combine 1/2 cake mix, water, eggs, margarine and brown sugar. Blend in remaining cake mix.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and soup together and spread over potatoes.
Cover with grated cheese.
Dot with desired amount of butter or oleo.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage, head down, until tender enough to separate leaves. Mix together meat, rice, onion, raisins or prunes, seasonings and 3 tablespoons of the tomato paste. Fill cabbage leaves and lay in large baking pan. Cover with remaining tomato paste, mixed with one can of water, the can of tomatoes, vinegar, brown sugar, gingersnaps and bay leaves. Cook, covered, for 3 to 4 hours at 325°. Serves 8 very hungry people or 12 not so hungry people.

title: pizza bread
directions: Cut bread into thin slices.
Mix tomato sauce and basil. Sprinkle any toppings of your choice on bread after spooning on the tomato sauce mixture, then sprinkle cheese on the very top. Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Fry chicken until brown.
Mix well all other ingredients (except sesame seed); cook until they boil.
Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes with can of mandarin oranges.
Sprinkle sesame seed on top.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stems and chop fine.
Microwave mushroom caps at Medium for 1 minute.
Microwave bacon at High until crisp (2 1/2 to 3 minutes).
Drain.
Add mushroom stems, onions, salt, pepper and red pepper sauce.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Stir in cream until smooth.
Microwave until thickened and smooth.
Fill each mushroom cap with bacon mixture and cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until cheese melts. Makes about 12 appetizers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add onion, sugar, salt, pepper, egg (add and beat quickly to avoid curdling), 1/2 stick oleo and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs to squash.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with another 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and another 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or microwave on Full power for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix jello and cake mix together.
Mix Wesson oil with eggs, one at a time.
Pour oil and egg and mix well.
Divide into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Use strawberry shortcake filling.

title: super pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: kathy's tang tea
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in a jar or other covered container. Use about 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of mix per 6 ounces of boiling water.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Hint:
Have lettuce dry so it doesn't get soggy.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a serving bowl. Heat vinegar and sugar until dissolved. Cool to lukewarm and pour over vegetables. Mix well and refrigerate until serving time.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Let rise in warm place, about 30 minutes or until soft and puffed. Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 or 8 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 9 to 11 buns.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl together and mix well. Grease and flour 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) cake pans.
Bake about 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fiasco
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato juice and chili mix; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add corn and rice.
This mixture is served over the chips on a plate, so it shouldn't be too runny.
You don't want it as thick as refried beans, either.
Adjust by cooking down a bit or adding a little water.
Heat cheese soup in saucepan and add Velveeta and tomatoes and green chiles; heat slowly.
Top meat mixture with cheese mixture.
In any order you wish, top meat mixture with any topping you would like on Mexican food.

title: danish apple bars
directions: Mix flour and salt. Cut in Crisco like pie dough.
Add egg yolk-milk mixture to crust.
Work well, divide dough in half. Roll to fit 18 x 12 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Place on sheet, sprinkle Rice Krispies over dough.

title: mushrooms supreme
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water and set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a small saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Blend in pepper, whipping cream and bouillon.
Stir into mushrooms.
Pour mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: m&m's party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/4 cup of the candies.
Save the remaining candies for decorating.
Drop dough from the teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove cookies to wire racks.
Cool completely before storing.
Enjoy!

title: cake icing
directions: Mix top 3 ingredients.
Then, add sugar slowly until the right thickness to spread.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: *You can also use 1/4 cup wine vinegar and 1/4 cup apple cider vinegar.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cream together the brown sugar and margarine.
Add the eggs and milk, sherry or wine.
Sift together the flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix the last 4 ingredients together.
Add all ingredients together; mix well.
Drop onto cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Do not have fruit and nuts too coarse.

title: cherry treasure mold
directions: Blend together the cream cheese and mayo.
Dissolve gelatins in boiling juice; stir into cream cheese mixture.
Add ginger ale. Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: cashew chicken stir-fry
directions: Blend together water, soy sauce, cornstarch, garlic and pepper. Set aside.
Heat oil in wok or skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and celery.
Stir-fry for 4 minutes or until chicken and celery are tender.
Add mushrooms and cashews; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Mix in soy mixture; cook and stir until sauce is thickened.
Serve with rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cool banana pudding(easy)
directions: Mix pudding mix according to directions on box.
Add Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Mix well.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Top with wafers.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses and margarine soften and mix well with electric mixer.
Chill for several hours.
Form into 2 balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: apple slaw
directions: Core, do not pare, apple; dice finely.
Immediately sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Toss together the cabbage, apple and carrot.
Mix salt, mayonnaise and water; toss with first mixture.
Sprinkle over paprika and some pepper, if desired.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown your ground beef and sausage together. Add cheese, oregano, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce. Put a spoonful of mixture onto rye bread. Heat until warm.

title: low-fat pudding pie
directions: Cook pudding as per directions on box.
Fill pie crust and chill for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Nestle morsels.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread in small pieces.
Mix other ingredients well and pour over bread.
Mix well. Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with milk, cream or whipped cream or plain.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the water. Sift salt, sugar and flour into a bowl. Make a well in the middle of flour mixture; add the egg whites and yeast water. Knead the dough. Divide the dough into 3 pieces. Use a food processor that kneads the dough or you can knead the dough by hand. Set aside the dough in bowls; cover and let the dough rise until it doubles in size (approximately 1 to 2 hours). Punch down and knead the dough again; cover and let the dough rise again for another hour. Sprinkle corn meal on a cookie sheet (prevents it from sticking). Form the dough into loaves and arrange on the cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: turkey and wild rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart lightly greased casserole, combine rice with seasoning packet, water, turkey, mushrooms, artichokes and pimento.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Top casserole with cheese.
Return to oven and bake, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes; boil for 15 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Beat eggs together.
Beat in flour which has been sifted several times.
This has to be beaten well to make it rise as no baking powder is used.
Bake slowly (about 300°).

title: carrot casserole
directions: Blend first three ingredients. Blend dry ingredients with carrot mixture. Pour into 2 quart greased baking dish. Bake uncovered at 400° for 15 minutes. Lower temperature to 350° and cook 45 minutes more.

title: coffee tin bread
directions: Let raisins, boiling water and soda sit overnight after mixing.
Grease three 1-pound coffee tins.
Mix sugar and flour and add oil slowly.
Mix with overnight raisin mixture.
Fill coffee tins half full.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Shake out of cans.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger.
Season to taste; add onion.
Drain excess grease off.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, margarine, Karo syrup and cream of tartar for 5 minutes.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Add syrup to popcorn (I use a large metal bowl).
Bake in metal bowl at 250° for about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
After it has cooled, if it is sticky, bake for a short while longer.
Should be crunchy when done.

title: bride's punch(serves 30)
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and water. Add lemonade and pineapple juice.
Freeze, stirring occasionally.

title: frosted spice cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add molasses, egg and milk; mix well.
Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in walnuts, raisins and dates, if wanted.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Roll dough out on a lightly floured surface about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken, corn, black bean and tomato salad
directions: Tear chicken into shreds or chop.
Combine with corn, beans and tomato in a bowl.
Heat oil in a small skillet.
Add garlic and saute until just beginning to color, about 30 seconds.
Add oregano and cumin; stir until fragrant, about 10 seconds.
Remove from heat.
Add vinegar and salt.
Pour over salad.
Add onions and parsley; toss gently to combine.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine, add remaining ingredients into 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white icing(excellent)
directions: Beat for 20 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: All ingredients must be fresh. Pound chicken breast to uniform size. Lightly oil and bread with fine bread crumbs. Put chicken on hot grill. While chicken is cooking, brown mushrooms and green onion in
butter and lemon. When chicken is done, pour mushrooms and green onion mixture over chicken. Serve with rice and green salad.

title: fluffy chocolate pie
directions: Mix together and layer in a dish.

title: peaches and cream cheese cake
directions: Beat the flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla pudding, butter, egg and milk for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 1/2-inch pie plate.
Place over batter the drained peaches.
Combine the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and juice.
Beat for 2 minutes, then spoon on top of peaches, 1-inch from the edge.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Mix jello and water.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Chill until it begins to set, then stir in whipped cream, cheese and nuts.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: church windows cookies
directions: In double boiler, melt oleo and chocolate chips.
Add vanilla. Stir in nuts.
Cool.
When lukewarm, fold in marshmallows.
Shape in foil overnight in refrigerator (roll in foil to long lengths before you refrigerate), then slice when set.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add fruit and nuts.
Put 1/2 of mixture in ring mold; chill until firmly set.
Spread with cream cheese or sour cream.
Spoon on second half of Jell-O.
Chill until firmly set.
Unmold.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Butter dish completely.
Spread rice evenly around dish.
Dot with butter (whole stick).
Salt and pepper chicken.
Arrange on top of rice.
Mix soups with water (1 1/2 cans).
Pour over chicken and rice until thoroughly saturated.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine condensed milk, evaporated milk, sugar, eggs, whipping cream, vanilla and fruit (if desired).
Pour into ice cream freezer and add whole milk to the fill line on container.
Makes a very rich, creamy ice cream.
This also freezes well if not all used at time of making.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Crumble 4 or 5 crackers for each layer.
Layer oysters, dotted with butter and soda crackers in a 1-quart buttered casserole. Reserve oyster liquor and pour over finished layers.
Pour half and half over all until it reaches top of casserole.
Let rest for 1 hour before baking in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: date balls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add crispy rice cereal and vanilla.
Form into small pecan-sized balls.
Roll in powdered sugar until coated.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: pickle fans
directions: These are for garnish to accent salads and platters.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix cereal, flour, sugar and soda in large bowl.
Add raisins, then add beaten eggs, shortening and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks and use when desired.
Bake in greased muffin tins (or paper lined) for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: west virginia trout
directions: Pour orange juice into microwave-safe baking dish.
Place fillets in dish and lightly spray fillet surface with vegetable spray.
In small bowl, combine tarragon, pepper and orange peel. Sprinkle on top of fish and pat in lightly.
Cover with plastic wrap and vent.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
May be baked in oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Do not cover.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
Per serving:
155 cal. 20% cal. from fat; 3.5 grams fat; 4 grams carbohydrate.

title: sour cream devil's food cake
directions: Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: prawns primavera
directions: Blanch the vegetables until just firm.
Saute the onions, garlic, basil and parsley in the oil.
Add the vegetables and prawns, tossing lightly until well heated.
Add the rest of the ingredients, holding back half of the cheese.
Add the heated pasta and mix completely.
Serve on heated plates and sprinkle the remaining cheese over the top.

title: flounder roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium-sized frying pan, saute scallops, onion, parsley and garlic in oil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and mix in cracker crumbs. Divide dressing equally, spreading evenly over fillets.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and few drops of lemon juice.
Roll each fillet, jelly roll fashion, and secure with toothpicks.
Brush each with melted butter.
Place on cookie sheet, cover lightly with foil and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove foil and cook 10 minutes more, or until fish flakes easily when touched with fork.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: seven layer vegetable salad
directions: Place lettuce in
large
bowl.
Then
add
celery, then green peppers, then
onions,
then green peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Cover
vegetables
with mayonnaise mixture, making sure to cover
completely.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then bacon crumbs and lastly place
egg
slices
on top and sprinkle with paprika to add color.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator and let set overnight.

title: garden variety pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into jelly roll pan and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix yogurt, salad dressing, Ricotta and ranch dressing mix.
Spread on cooled crust; top with slices and small pieces of favorite vegetables in layers and sprinkle with seasoned salt (if desired).
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and garnish with olives.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: potato casserole #3
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and put in a 13 x 9-inch greased casserole.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: stromboli's
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw bread dough.
Break four pieces out of bread dough.
Put shortening on bread dough before thawing. Roll each piece of dough out.
Put pepperoni, ham and shredded Mozzarella cheese on dough.
Fold over and pinch dough all the way around stromboli.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and when cooked, mash with a masher.
Carefully add the butter, flour and extra milk or cream just before serving.
Heat thorough.

title: vienna and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain and blanch in cold water. Drain thoroughly.
Combine celery, pickles, onion and Vienna sausages; mix with macaroni.
Blend mayonnaise, pickle juice, salt and pepper; add to macaroni mixture and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Combine pretzel crumbs and melted butter and firmly press on bottom and 1-inch up sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Set prepared pan aside.
Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy; gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add 3/4 cup peanut butter, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; turn oven off and partially open door.
Leave cheesecake in oven for 30 minutes.
Combine sour cream, 3 tablespoons peanut butter and 1/2 cup sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Spread sour cream mixture over warm cheesecake.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: cornish hens and rice
directions: Spread rice in a 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden, stirring occasionally.
Combine salad dressing mix with water and soup.
Stir in rice.
Cut hens in half lengthwise.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place cut side down on rice.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 1 hour; uncover and bake 30 minutes longer or until rice and hens are tender.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Remove the leaves from the stalk of the cabbage, then pare down the ribs so that the leaves are fairly flat.
Put the leaves into boiling salted water and cook until half done.

Lay two or three large leaves together, spread with stuffing and roll up. Tie them with thread (previously boiled) or secure with skewers. Heat the fat or the diced bacon; put in the cabbage rolls and brown slightly on all sides.
Add water as required and a little gravy, if available.
Thicken the cooking liquid with cornstarch powder, blended with the water; season to taste and poured over the cabbage rolls.
Cooking time: about 45 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Put ground beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic in skillet with a little bacon grease and brown.
After meat mixture has browned, add tomato soup and 1 can of water to the mixture and stir well. A little Worcestershire sauce may be added, if desired.
Heat thoroughly on low heat.

title: molded chicken salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water and then add the ginger ale.
Pour into bowl and cool.
When slightly jelled, add balance of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold rubbed with cooking oil.
Sliced olives may be placed in bottom of mold before salad is poured in.

title: cream cheese biscuits
directions: Cut cream cheese and butter into flour until crumbly.
Add milk; stir to moisten.
Put on floured surface.
Knead 4 to 5 times.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together.
Simmer until thick, 1 hour or more.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: In large soup crock pot cook onions and garlic in butter until tender.
Blend in soup, cream cheese and milk.
Add chicken and corn.
Sprinkle in cayenne.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring frequently, as it tends to stick.
Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and place in 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with turkey or chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over broccoli mixture and top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: milk chocolate icing
directions: Melt bitter chocolate and butter together and add to the powdered sugar.
Add warm water, a spoonful at a time, until a smooth paste is formed.
Cut milk chocolate in small pieces; melt and add to ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Add water until the proper consistency is reached for spreading.

title: lemon dream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, mix Eagle Brand and lemonade.
After mixed well, spoon in softened Cool Whip.
After all the ingredients are mixed well, spoon in pie crust.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: baked italian tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tomatoes in half.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, garlic salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: vegetables in cream sauce
directions: Heat butter.
Stir in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring until smooth.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened.
Add salt, pepper and vegetables.
Heat.
Makes 6 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: cold raspberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch and cook until clear. Stir in Jello.
Cool.
Fold in raspberries.
Pour into prepared pie shell. Chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
This recipe can be modified to the taste or availability of ingredients of the chef.
It can also be made large (lasagna pan large) by doubling or tripling the recipe.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients (except crust) and cook until slightly thickened. Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff and pour on top of pie.
Sprinkle with coconut and return to oven to brown.

title: breakfast-in-a-dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare bacon in skillet over medium heat; drain.
In large saucepan or stockpot, combine hash brown patties, bouillon cubes and water.
Cover and place over medium-low heat until patties are thawed and crumbled.
Remove from heat.
Add bacon, margarine, cheese, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients together until margarine and cheese have melted.
Gradually add egg substitute to mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into a 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour or until mixture is firmly set in center.

title: fruit cup
directions: Peel cantaloupe; cut into chunks.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.

title: sweet potato pudding *
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, ginger, butter and sweet milk together. Peel potatoes and put in cool water to keep from turning dark. Grate potato and add to mixture as you grate each potato, to keep bright.
Grease a dish (7 x 13-inch) with butter and cook at 250° for 30 or 40 minutes, or until stops bubbling up, then cook at 400° until a nice shade of brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Sift all dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add nuts.
Pour into pans and bake 1 hour.

title: caramel nut icing
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add the 1/2 cup of brown sugar.
Stir well.
Add 2 cups powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts, if desired.
(Coconut may be substituted.)

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Dice onion and pepper.
Add to spaghetti.
Pour dressing (all) and seasoning in next.
Mix together well.
Cube tomato for top.
Store in refrigerator.
Best if set in refrigerator overnight or at least a few hours.

title: rye bread boat
directions: Hollow out round loaf of rye bread; fill with dip.
Tear bread into chunks; serve with dip.

title: little ruthie's queen ann cake
directions: Mix the chopped dates, boiling water and baking soda; let stand.
Cream together the sugar, butter and egg.
Add the vanilla and salt.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Alternate mixtures with sugar and butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes in an 11 x 7-inch pan or 11 x 9-inch pan.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sour cream, eggs, sugar and oleo.
Then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: goof proof microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Microwave 2 minutes. Stir.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: fried apples
directions: Put all in frying pan (iron).
Cover.
Steam until apples are tender and water cooked out.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix beef, onion, salt, pepper and rice together.
Shape the mixture into about 1 dozen meatballs.
In pressure cooker or deep saucepan, heat 1 can tomato soup and 1 can water.
Wait until boiling and drop meatballs into tomato mixture.
Pressure 13 minutes or simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Layer Twinkies on bottom of 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
On top of Twinkies, put defrosted strawberries.
Allow to sit in refrigerator overnight.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baklava
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare honey syrup by heating sugar, water and lemon juice to boiling.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in honey.
Cool.
Mix nuts and spices.
Brush bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan (for puff pastry) or 15 x 10-inch jelly-roll pan (for phyllo dough) with some of the margarine.
Line bottom of pan with pastry or dough.
Brush with margarine.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of nut mixture.
Repeat with another layer of pastry or dough, margarine and nuts.
Layer remaining pastry or dough on top of last layer.
Brush with margarine.
With a sharp knife, cut pastry into 8 lengthwise strips, 1/2-inch deep.
Make diagonal cuts across strips, 1/2-inch deep and 2-inches wide.
Bake until golden brown (35 minutes for pastry and 1 to 1 1/4 hours for phyllo dough).
Place pan on wire rack; pour syrup over top.
Cool.
Cut along scored lines.
Yield: about 36 pieces.

title: coconut pie(makes 3)
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and margarine in a large bowl.
Mix in cream, coconut and flavoring.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: fudge pie
directions: Blend together 1 stick butter, 1 cup sugar, 2 whole eggs, 1/2 cup sifted flour, 1 square chocolate and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch plate (glass).
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Place rice and milk in top of double boiler.
Cook covered for 45 minutes.
Beat egg yolks, honey and salt together.
Stir some rice mixture into yolks.
Add yolks to hot mixture and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Whip egg whites until fluffy and then fold into rice mixture.
Add cinnamon and raisins, if desired.
Serve warm or chilled.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 1 or 2 hours before serving.
Serve on crackers or chips.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all (except vanilla) in baking bowl.
Bake at 325° until rice is cooked.
Add vanilla while still warm.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake
mix according to package.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: friendship cake
directions: Use 1 gallon glass jug; add starter from a friend (if you have any), 2 1/2 cups sugar and 1 large can peaches (chopped); let stand for 10 days, stirring each day with a wooden spoon.
(Do not refrigerate.)
After 10 days, add 2 1/2 cups sugar and large can crushed pineapple.
Do not drain; let stand 10 days, stirring each day.
After 10 days, add 2 1/2 cups sugar, a large can fruit cocktail and 1 (10 ounce) jar maraschino cherries, chopped.
After 10 days, drain fruit and save juice for a friend.
Makes 4 to 5 starters, 1 pint each.
There is enough fruit for 3 cakes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Trim crust off bread, roll each slice flat with rolling pin. Mix cheese and mayonnaise to spreading consistency.
Spread each slice with mixture.
Add asparagus and roll up.
Place in buttered casserole and brush each roll with melted butter.
Place under broiler until brown.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs (well beaten).
Add soda, dissolved in hot water.
Add half of the flour.
Add mincemeat and rest of flour and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Remove while hot and place in covered bowl; keep covered.
Delicious.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a casserole; alternate ingredients in layers.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: cold salad dressing
directions: Mix together.
Very good for potato and macaroni, too.
Omit milk for these.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat until smooth.
Fry on a hot griddle.

title: cherry pie filling dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add next 2 ingredients, then add Cool Whip and mix well.
You may use more marshmallows and pecans if you like.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Separate yolks from whites.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add egg whites to yolks.
Beat in sugar.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture, a small amount at a time.
Scald milk.
Add butter to milk and let melt.
Add milk and butter to first mixture and blend well.
Bake in moderate oven, 325° to 350°, for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate a few hours.
Goes great with Swiss cheese crackers.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut.
Let stand until firm.

title: italian cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese, chop onions, and beef finely.
Mix well add 2 Tbsp pecans, mix, and shape in balls.
Roll in pecans.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first nine ingredients (omitting oil).
Stir in okra. Pour oil in skillet to depth of 2 inches.
Heat to 350°.
Drop by tablespoons; fry to golden brown.
Frozen okra may be substituted for fresh.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: lazy lentil stew
directions: Add dry
soup
mix to boiling water in a 2 quart saucepan. Lower
heat
to
simmer and add dry lentils, followed by cilantro. Simmer 5 minutes and add carrots.
When carrots are nearly tender,
add
tomatoes
and
mushrooms.
Total cooking time: 25 minutes.
For best results, prepare the previous day and refrigerate.
Serve
hot
with
a
dollop of chilled plain yogurt.

title: easy chocolate pudding(low-fat)
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Stir in the milk and add vanilla. Cook until thickened.
Refrigerate.

title: pan de casa
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding water to form a dough. Use half of dough and roll out to thick, round circle and place in a cake pan.
Do the same with the other half.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned.

title: fantasy fruit salad
directions: Combine all and enjoy!!!

title: marinara sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add parsley and onion.
Slowly add tomatoes.
Stir to break up tomatoes.
Add bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer sauce over low heat for about 15 minutes for flavors to blend.
Add fresh, finely chopped basil leaves, if desired.
Serve with any type pasta.

title: grill barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef, onion, salt and pepper, stirring with fork until meat loses it red color.
Blend in flour.
Add water, then Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: to make sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Refrigerate in a covered container.
Mixture will thicken.
One cup plus 2 tablespoons equals the 15 ounce can recipes require.

title: heavenly dirt
directions: You will need an 8-inch flowerpot, silk flowers and gummy worms.

title: apple pie
directions: Clean and slice the apples.
Mix all dry ingredients and pour over apples; mix well.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Add 2 tablespoons oleo.
Top with another crust; cut slits in top crust. If apples are not tart, add 1 tablespoon lemon juice to apples. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cajun oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Cut potatoes into wedges. In a large bowl, combine oil, hot sauce, thyme, paprika and cumin. Toss potatoes in dressing and spread out in a single layer on a nonstick cookie sheet. Season wedges with salt and pepper and roast for 20 minutes, turning once. Yield: 4 servings.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut a slice off top of tomato.
Scoop out and reserve center. Combine bread and dressings with 1 tablespoon of the oil and 2 tablespoons of the reserved tomato liquid.
Fill tomatoes with this mixture.
Place in a shallow pan and sprinkle with remaining oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: warm seafood spread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, crab, milk, horseradish and onion; mix well.
Spread in 9-inch pie pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with almonds and garnish with parsley.
Serve warm with crackers. Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: cranberry-apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry (for 2 crust pie).
Preheat oven to 425°.
Stir together sugar, flour and spice. In pastry lined pan, alternate layers of apples, cranberries and sugar mixture, beginning and ending with apples. Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and cut slits in crust. Seal and flute edges.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Cool.

title: my grandkid's favorite casserole
directions: Saute hamburg with onion.
Cook noodles until tender; add to vegetables.
Cook carrots; drain.
Heat peas; drain.
Blend meat with soup and milk.

title: sandra's vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into a tube pan. Bake in a 300° preheated oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add currants, coconut and nuts. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
When cold, wrap and refrigerate.
Cut in thin slices and serve with cream cheese, butter, cottage cheese or other spread.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Mold to form a loaf in a pan.
Pour tomato sauce over meat loaf and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until it reaches desired doneness.

title: frosty squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the first 4 ingredients and spread evenly in a baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle 2/3 of this in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine the egg whites, sugar, berries and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Beat with mixer on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Fold in whipping cream and spoon over nut mixture. Top with remaining crumbs and freeze overnight.
Cut into squares and served topped with a tablespoon Cool Whip and half strawberry.

title: shrimp scampi supreme
directions: For Marinade:
Combine the first 6 ingredients in jar.
Cover; shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over shrimp.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain shrimp; reserve marinade.
Broil shrimp 5 to 6 inches from heat for 3 minutes, brushing with marinade.
Turn shrimp; broil second side about 3 minutes, or until shrimp are cooked, also brushing with marinade.
Serve with rice pilaf.
Serves 4.

title: eggs strata
directions: Combine together (can be done the night before) and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: california fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in order given. Grease a Bundt pan or equivalent (9 x 9-inch, etc.)
Bake approximately 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Simmer for 20 minutes and remove spice bag.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and 2 to 2 1/2 cups of cheese.
In baking dish, combine cooked broccoli and cheese mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls and chill about 2 hours.
Mix chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls on toothpicks in chocolate mixture and leave part of top bare.
Cool on waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: italian cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbages and carrots in a medium size mixing bowl.
Mix dressing as directed on package.
Add the sugar. Shake up until dissolved. Add to the slaw mixture.

title: hamburgers baked in foil
directions: Brown hamburger and drain on paper towels.
Saute green pepper, celery and onion; add to hamburger in a large bowl.
Add mayonnaise, catsup, dill pickle, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and salt and pepper.
Mix well and spread on 1/2 of a hamburger bun. Place a slice of cheese, if desired.
Cover with bun top.
Wrap in squares of aluminum foil (heavy is best).
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.
(Stays hot for about 30 to 45 minutes.)

title: empanadas
directions: Cook the hamburger, sausage, onion and garlic in a large skillet until brown, stirring frequently.
Add the chili powder, salt, bread, tomato paste and water and mix well.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Roll out the pastry on a floured surface and cut into 6-inch circles.
Fold over and crimp the edge with a fork. Brush with butter and place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: country candied yams
directions: Cut up sweet potatoes.
Mix sugar, butter, cinnamon, vanilla flavor and nutmeg while the sweet potatoes are cooking.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain hamburger and bacon.
Drain all beans a little.
Mix together ketchup, salt, vinegar, kidney beans, brown sugar, mustard, medium can beans and butter beans.
Add all to meat. Bake for one hour at 300°.

title: indian rice
directions: Prepare rice according	to basic rice recipe except for baking.
Stir in
all
ingredients	except chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for
minutes.
Remove rice from oven and stir in chicken.
Return to oven and bake an additional ten minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Yields 2 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crackers and oleo and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks oleo and powdered sugar for no less than 15 minutes.
Spread on unbaked crumb crust.
Next layer first the sliced bananas, pineapple, whipped topping, cherries and nuts.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until almost done.
Cool, pare and grate potatoes and layer in greased 10 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer of potatoes, layer of cheese and onions.
Cover with half of soup and sour cream.
Add another layer of potatoes and cheese. Spread remaining soup and sour cream and salt.
Dot with margarine.
Can be refrigerated overnight.
May need small amount of milk when baking.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 2 hours.
Can use all half and half instead of sour cream and soup.

title: yams
directions: Bake potatoes; skin, slice and place in a bowl.
In a saucepan, add sugar and water; boil to soft ball form.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour over sliced potatoes and bake 1/2 hour at 350° (uncovered).

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until candy forms medium soft ball.
(Do not stir too much or it will turn to sugar.)
Remove from heat and set pan in cold water and beat until starts setting up.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook and chop chicken. Place in buttered baking dish. Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over the chicken. Crush the crackers and cover the cream mixture. Melt the butter and pour on the crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place vegetables (frozen) in casserole; sprinkle cheese on top.
Crumble crackers and put on top of cheese, and drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: For orange eggs, boil in onion skins.

title: lib's cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage and steam approximately 2 minutes.
Put cabbage in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour undiluted soup over this.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Crumble crackers and put on top.
Melt margarine and drizzle on mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice and soup mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup and water together and pour over rice.
Top with meat.
Cover with foil or lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and brown for 10 to 15 minutes.
Just right to bake while in church!

title: e-z coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream butter, cream cheese, and sugar until light and fluffy, add the eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk until smooth after each addition.
Spread onto greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: baquette bread bites
directions: Mix all together (first five items). Slice bread in 1-inch slices. Spread mixture on bread and bake at 360° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: frosted maple-pecan white chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda in medium bowl. Beat brown sugar, butter and shortening until creamy. Add eggs, vanilla and maple flavoring. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels and chopped pecans. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes (or until light golden brown). When cool, spread with Maple Frosting and top with 1/2 pecan. Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: creamed chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Cook chicken and strip from bones. Add chicken, cream of mushroom soup and water together and heat. Add to rice.
Serve.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: stir-fry veggies
directions: Stir-fry first 4 ingredients in large skillet with butter. Cook, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, garlic salt and cheese; cook an additional 5 minutes.

title: ham, potato, cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Beginning with potatoes, layer in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Cover; cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: pork chops with creamy mustard sauce
directions: In hot oil, cook chops until brown on both sides.
Remove from pan.
In drippings on medium heat, cook carrots and onion until tender.
Stir in wine, mustard, salt and pepper, thyme and 1 cup of water.
Return pork chops to skillet.
On medium heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until chops are fork-tender.
Remove chops to platter.
In a cup, mix milk and flour until blended.
Gradually add to skillet. Simmer until mixture is thickened.
Pour mixture over chops and serve.

title: transparent pie or puddings
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, beating with wire whisk. Add vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust or tart shells. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 300° until set and light brown.

title: one egg cake
directions: Combine all items and mix well.
Pour into desired pan and bake until golden brown.
Frost with your favorite icing.
Oven should be at 350°.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box.
Then stir strawberry pie filling in.
Mix well.
Then add crushed pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until well chilled.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat; add sugar.
Cook until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Peel bananas; slice crosswise, then quarter each piece lengthwise.
Quarter each pineapple slice. Stir bananas, pineapple and cinnamon into brown sugar sauce. Cook over medium heat until bananas are slightly soft; baste constantly with sauce.
Add liqueur; stir gently.
Place rum in small, long-handled pan and heat until just warm.
Ignite and pour over fruit.
Serve immediately over ice cream.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Fry onions and celery in 1 teaspoon margarine.
Mix all ingredients, except bread cubes and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer and chill before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: stir-fried red cabbage
directions: Cook onion in melted oleo about 10 minutes.
Add cabbage, coat with butter.
Add broth, salt and pepper.
Over medium heat, cook, stirring often, about 8 to 10 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Remove pan from heat and stir in vinegar, brown sugar and orange peel.

title: pecan candy cake
directions: Combine fruits, sprinkle with the flour.
Toss to coat well. Add pecans and coconut; toss to mix.
Add condensed milk and stir to mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch tube pan, smoothing top.
Bake in 250° slow oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan on rack.
Remove; wrap tightly in foil.
Refrigerate at least 2 weeks.
Cake cuts best when cold.
Slice very thin with serrated knife.

title: fresh peach chutney
directions: In a medium saucepan combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil, stir to dissolve sugar. Reduce heat to low, simmer, uncovered, stir once in a while, for 45 minutes or until chutney is thick and most of the liquid is gone. Remove from heat. Makes 1 1/2 pts. Process as for canning or refrigerate.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, molasses and water.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Mix thoroughly and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick beef minestrone
directions: In large saucepan, saute meat, onion and garlic; drain off fat. Add broth, beans, tomatoes, bay leaf, basil and pepper; simmer 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup macaroni (elbow or shells, small) and bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Serve piping hot, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: grilled breakfast quail
directions: Combine butter, garlic powder and salt; brush on all sides of quail.
Wrap 1 slice bacon around each quail; secure with wooden picks.

title: maple oat banana bread
directions: Grease a tube pan and dust with oatmeal.
Combine flour, oats and soda; toss.
In mixing bowl, cream oil and sugar.
Mix in bananas, eggs and walnuts.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix on low speed until thoroughly blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan.
Cool on rack completely.
Drizzle with Maple Glaze.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix pecans, coconut, sugar, milk, vanilla and melted butter in large bowl.
Roll into small balls; let chill.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler.
Stick toothpicks into balls and dip in chocolate.

title: italian lasagne(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Brown sausage and meat; drain off fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt (1 teaspoon), tomatoes, tomato paste and wine.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Cook lasagne noodles; drain.
Beat eggs; add Ricotta or cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt (1 teaspoon) and pepper.
Blend well.
Layer 1/2 noodles in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with 1/2 cheese mixture; add 1/2 Mozzarella and 1/2 meat sauce. Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
This freezes beautifully.

title: merry berry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container and chill in refrigerator.
Just before serving, pour into punch bowl.
Float orange and lime slices on top.
Makes 22 (6 oz.) servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water, 25-30 minutes or until tender. Peel and slice.
Add onion.
In large skillet, fry bacon.
Drain. Return 1/4 cup fat to skillet.
Stir flour, sugar, margarine, salt, and pepper into skillet.
Add vinegar and 1 cup of water. Bring to boil, stirring.
Remove from heat and add sour cream. Add potatoes, onions, half of bacon, stirring gently.
Sprinkle with rest of bacon and parsley.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: broccoli cheddar dip
directions: In sieve, rinse frozen broccoli under warm water to thaw. Squeeze lightly to drain well.
In medium bowl, combine broccoli, soup mix, mayonnaise, sour cream and cheese.
Stir thoroughly. Slice lid from top of loaf; hollow out center and fill with dip mixture.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut bread from center into cubes of finger-food pieces and serve with dip.
Makes 12 to 16 appetizer servings.

title: martha's peach cobblerroswell, new mexico
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour mixture into baking dish on top of the melted margarine.
Place the peaches on top of the mixture.
Then pour the peach juice on top.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.
Crust will come to the top.

title: veal scaloppine a la marsala
directions: Dust veal with flour.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Heat butter and oil in frying pan; saute meat over medium flame.
Allow meat about 3 minutes on first side; turn and cook on other side 4 to 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, wine and stock.
Cover; simmer gently over low heat for about 10 minutes, turning meat after 5 minutes so that it cooks evenly.
Remove meat to platter; boil down sauce until it is half as much.
Adjust seasonings.
Pour sauce over veal and serve.

title: morning glorious muffins
directions: Combine flour, soda,
sugar,
cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon salt. In another
bowl, combine carrot, apple, coconut, dates and raisins.
Stir in
beaten
eggs,
oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring
until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin pans.
Bake at 375°
for
to 20 minutes.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Beat in other ingredients, one at a time.
Add flour, blending well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork and sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peppermint cupcake cones
directions: Prepare cake mix batter as directed on package.
Fill cones 2/3 full with batter.
Place on baking sheet and bake in moderate 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.
Prepare a fluffy white frosting.
Blend in peppermint extract.
Swirl frosting on cake cones.
Decorate as desired with colored sugars, red jelly beans and/or gumdrops.

title: pralines
directions: Cook and stir margarine, milk and sugars to soft-ball stage (235°).
Add vanilla and pecans.
Beat until thick.
Drop onto waxed paper or foil.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Put in buttered casserole with crumbs. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and fruit filling and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: lime mint salad
directions: Don't drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple, mints and marshmallows and cover with plastic wrap.
Stir occasionally.
Leave in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Then fold in Cool Whip. Put in muffin cups in muffin tins and freeze.

title: maple and spice cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, raisins, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and peel.
Mix well. Add milk, syrup, margarine and eggs.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 400° for 17 to 22 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Yields 9 servings.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Cook to make syrup, about 3 minutes; cool.
Add frozen orange juice to pineapple juice.
Add bananas, then freeze.
Take from freezer 2 hours before serving and mash with potato masher.
Add 7-Up and serve.
Makes approximately 5 quarts or 35 punch cups.
Gold in color.

title: 7-up salad(congealed)
directions: Drain the pineapple.
Measure juice and add water to make 1 cup.
Heat juice and dissolve the jello.
Stir in the marshmallows. Add the cold 7-Up and drained pineapple.
Chill until it sets.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix in a 2 qt. saucepan sugar, cornstarch, salt, evaporated milk and whole milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens & boils for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Slowly pour half of the hot mixture into eggs & stir until that mixture is completely incorporated. Then pour the egg mixture into the pot with the other half of pudding and continue to cook on medium heat until it reaches boiling stage again. Add cream cheese & mix thoroughly (use a hand mixer). It will dissolve the cream cheese better & make the pudding lighter & creamier. Remove from heat & add vanilla & butter. Keep using hand mixer until all is blended. Let pudding stand for 15 minutes, but while still warm pour half of pudding in pie shell & layer with bananas. Then pour remainder of pudding on top. When pie is completely cooled, top with fresh whipped cream and garnish with sliced almonds.

title: doris kramer's potato pancakes
directions: Grate the potatoes, leaving in all liquid. Add the eggs, salt, onion and pepper.
Drop by spoonful into 1/8-inch hot oil.
Fry quickly on each side.
Drain on heavy paper.
Should be very crisp. Serve at once. Good with applesauce or sour cream.

title: crab-spinach quiche
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed, folding gently to blend. Divide into 3 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pesto pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Soak in enough water to cover.
Microwave 1 minute; let stand.
Saute mushrooms and garlic in oil.
Spread pesto over crust.
Drain tomatoes and spread over pesto.
Crumble Feta cheese over pizza. Top with mushrooms.
Grate fresh Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes (follow Boboli instructions).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions in 2-quart bowl. Spread dressing over top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: basic yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk to scalding. Remove from heat, add butter, sugar and salt to milk. Dissolve yeast in warm water (about 5 minutes). Add 1 cup flour to milk mixture. Beat about 1 minute until smooth. Stir dissolved yeast into milk mixture. Add eggs and beat again until smooth. Add remaining flour, mixing thoroughly. Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes). Form dough into a ball and place dough in a large bowl that you have rubbed with Crisco. Cover bowl with clean cloth and place in area away from drafts and let rise until double in bulk (approximately 1 1/1- 2 hours). Punch down and mold into desired shapes. Make 3 balls for each roll using a muffin tin that has been greased, and place 3 balls snugly into each one.
Using a pastry brush coat each roll with butter then let rise again until light. Bake in preheated 400 oven for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
This will yield about 2 dozen rolls. Serve warm.

title: rigatoni in diablo clam sauce(hot and spicy!)
directions: Begin cooking rigatoni.
Saute garlic in heated oil and butter.
Add chili powder and stir over medium heat for 1 minute. Add paprika, pepper, cayenne and tomatoes; lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
After 10 minutes, add clams, juice and lemon juice. Simmer 5 more minutes.

title: fun cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Roll out on floured board; cut with cookie cutter or make 1 round roll and slice.
Bake in oven at 325° about 6 or 8 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Spread potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chopped onion over them.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese and milk in pan.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Spread over potatoes.
Spread crumbled bacon. Mix corn flakes and melted oleo; put on top.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and oleo, then bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and peanut butter. Stir until thick.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut into squares when set.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Spread on top of cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix to smooth batter. Melt 1 stick butter/margarine in baking pan (approximately 9 x 13-inches).
Pour batter over melted butter/margarine.
Pour fruit and juice (up to 1/2 cup) over batter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: lazy cook's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or casserole dish.
Stir milk, sugar and flour together in mixing bowl.
(The batter will be thin.)
Pour fruit into baking pan with the butter.
Add batter.
Bake in a 475° oven until brown.

title: old fashion spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour boiling water over corn meal.
Stir to keep from lumping until cooled slightly and blended.
Stir in buttermilk.
Blend in sugar and soda.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni shells until tender.
Mix water chestnuts, green pepper, onion, pimento, soup, mushrooms and sour cream.
Combine mixture with macaroni.
Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: In a double boiler, melt stick of margarine and add cubed cream cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix together the soup mix, apricot preserves, Russian dressing and apricot juice.
Put apricots in a large casserole dish with chicken.
Pour mixture over chicken breasts.
Bake 1 hour covered, then uncover and brown.
Last 5 minutes put 1 apricot on each chicken breast.
Serve over rice.

title: pizza dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix in sour cream and Italian seasoning. Spread in x 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour pizza sauce over top.
Layer pepperoni and any other desired toppings over sauce.
Cover all with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.
Serve warm.
Dip with bread sticks or crackers.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream
the butter or margarine and sugar together.
Add egg, molasses,
cinnamon,
ginger
and cloves.
Mix together. Add flour, baking soda, salt and water.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: horseradish relish
directions: Wash horseradish roots thoroughly and remove the brown outer skin.
(A vegetable peeler is useful in removal of outer skin.) The roos may be grated or cut into small cubes and put through a food chopper or a blender.
Combine ingredients.
Pack into clean jars.
Seal tightly.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 2 jars (1/2 pint each).

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and nuts.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Place in layers in greased 2-quart casserole.
Garnish with green pepper slices.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: three milks cake
directions: Cut cakes into 6 slices each.
Combine milks and salt in a large bowl and stir well; set aside.
Lay cake slices in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour milk mixture evenly over cake slices; cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and spread thawed whipped topping over cake.
Chill for additional 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with fresh fruit or your favorite pie filling.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: easy and quick jelly roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and gradually add sugar and water. Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and gradually add to the batter.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 11 1/2 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 325° to 350° not over 15 minutes. Turn out on a cloth sprinkled with powdered sugar. Trim end edges.
Spread with jelly or jam.
Roll while cake is warm, wrapping it in the cloth.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before slicing.

title: french beef loaf
directions: Saute in oil, the chopped green peppers, onion and celery. Drain.
Add hamburger and Cheddar cheese soup.
Take French bread and cut in half lengthwise.
Hollow bread out of center of loaf. (Break up some of bread into meat mixture.)
Spoon meat mixture into hollowed center.
Put top back on and bake approximately 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: decadent fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
