Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Add 2 bars melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a heavily greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine.
Mix flour with margarine.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend in potato by mashing it slightly against the side of pan with fork. In a separate bowl, combine 1/4 cup evaporated skim milk with cornstarch until smooth.
Stir cornstarch mixture and remaining evaporated milk into broth mixture, cooking and stirring until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir one minute more, then gradually add cheeses, stirring until melted.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger and bacon; drain and set aside.
After hamburger and bacon have drained, mix all ingredients and cook in crock-pot on low for 7 hours.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry in 2 tablespoons butter about 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Simmer hamburger, onion, salt and pepper. Cream in blender the cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream. Add chopped peppers and green onions.
Layer noodles, meat and cheese sauce.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple pan dowdy
directions: Cream sugar, shortening together and then add eggs. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and mix in creamed mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
This makes a thick batter.
Bake in oblong 9x13 pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Gets crusty on top.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies, using blender or food processor.
Set aside.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan:
pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, then cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over pretzel mixture.
Prepare jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries (juice and all).
Chill until cool, then pour over cream cheese mixture and set.
Terrific made with orange jello and mandarin oranges.

title: helen's chicken casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of stuffing mix on bottom of casserole dish.
Put chicken on.
Combine liquids and pour on.
Place remainder of stuffing mix.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add 3 to 4 slices toasted bread, if desired.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Sprinkle tenderloin with peppers. Put in a heavy duty Ziploc bag. Mix soy sauce, bourbon and garlic and pour over meat. Close bag and let sit for 2 hours at room temperature.

title: italian mint sauce
directions: Mash garlic with salt to form paste.
Add mint leaves and crush well.
Add tomatoes, olive oil and pepper.
Continue to press until combined well and forms a thick sauce.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together in a deep bowl peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove and stir; continue to cook 4 minutes more.
Remove and add vanilla flavoring and butter or margarine; mix well.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove and add baking soda; stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto a lightly buttered cookie sheet pan and spread out.
Cool.
Break into small pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: molded cantaloupe balls
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in orange juice and ginger.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Stir in melon balls.
Pour into 6 individual molds and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Unmold to serve. Serves 6.

title: grandma barbara's chicken soup
directions: Wash chicken; prepare vegetables.
Fill 4-quart pot with cold water; bring to boil (add all ingredients just before water come to full boil).
Skim any fat which rises to top.
Turn heat to medium; stir briefly.
Cook at medium to medium-low heat for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add water to maintain original level.
Remove all bones from chicken.
Strain, cool and refrigerate.
Heat and enjoy!!

title: classic omelet(microwave dish)
directions: Place butter in a 9-inch micro-type pie plate.
Use High cycle and cook for 30 seconds, or until melted.
Beat remaining ingredients in bowl.
Pour into pie plate.
Cover with waxed paper.
Use High cycle and cook 6 to 8 1/2 minutes, stirring once during cooking time.
Let stand, covered, for 1 to 2 minutes. Fold in half to serve.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Beat butter on medium speed until creamy. Add sugar, egg and vanilla, beat well. Add flour one cup at a time until mixed well. Dough will be soft. Do not refrigerate. Fill cookie press with dough. Press cookies onto baking sheet. Bake for 10 -12 minutes or until firm. Do not let them get brown.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Cook until softened.
If you would like it sweeter, add 3 tablespoons honey.

title: four layer dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Combine flour, pecans and margarine. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french fried shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp; beat smooth.
Dry shrimp well; dip into batter.
Fry in hot deep fat (375°) until golden brown.
Drain.

title: peach pie
directions: Place peaches in bottom of baking dish.
Put bread crumbs over peaches and then spread eggs over this.
Melt butter and mix with flour and sugar.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, taco seasoning and cream cheese together. Spread in dish.
Top with vegetables.
Good with tortilla chips.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together and let set in the refrigerator overnight.
Serve with Doritos.

title: "ooy gooy cake"
directions: Mix together butter, egg and cake mix and pat in bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
Mix and pour cream cheese, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla over the 1st layer.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
(Won't look done, but it will fall.)

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Place peppers in a large pot.
Add sugar, vinegar and water. Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool for 20 minutes.
Add Certo; mix well and replace pot on heat.
Allow jelly to come to a full boil; remove from heat.
Stir well and pour into jelly glasses.
Seal with paraffin when jelly has cooled.
Makes 5-6 pint jars.

title: whole wheat stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers.
Dice pulp and reserve.
Cook zucchini boats for 3 minutes.

title: overnight french toast(makes 6 servings)
directions: Spread butter over bottom on large, heavy baking pan with 1-inch high sides.
Arrange bread slices in pan.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt to blend in large bowl.
Pour mixture over bread.
Turn bread slices to coat.
Cover with plastic; refrigerate overnight.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Cream butter and milk; add vanilla and sifted sugar.
Roll out on biscuit board 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with peanut butter. Roll up like jelly roll.
Put in refrigerator until firm enough to cut.

title: black-eyed pea enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas 2 at a time in shortening.
Stack and keep covered until ready to use.
Drain black-eyed peas and mash with a fork.
Add oregano, cumin, salt and pepper, 1/4 pound cheese and 1/2 cup chopped onion.
Place 3 tablespoons mixture on each tortilla and roll up and place in baking dish or pan. Pour on the hot dog sauce and remaining onion and cheese.
Place in oven at 300° until cheese is melted.
May be served with shredded lettuce and tomato wedges.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together and put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: unbelieveable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and make into balls. Flatten with fork on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well; chill.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix together, then add flour.
Press mixture into sprayed jelly-roll pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Glaze while hot.

title: german fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt, evaporated milk and butter in heavy 4-quart cooker. Cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a heavy boil. Start timing and cook 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, nuts last.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Cool completely.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Combine sugar (1 teaspoon), yeast, water and eggs. Let stand 5 minutes. Beat 2 minutes on low speed of electric mixer and set aside.

title: incredible carrot cake
directions: In mixer beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Blend well.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; mix well.
Pour in carrots and walnuts; mix.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans and bake at 350° for 42 to 48 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: beef and bean barbecue casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Add salt, pork and beans and barbecue sauce and stir until well blended; heat until bubbly.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese; bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashion bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk. Mix remaining ingredients together and stir into crumb mixture. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes. You can also microwave this on high for 5-7 minutes. It is done if knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Into a large bowl, mix the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in the carrots, raisins, nuts and apple.
In a bowl, beat the eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix (stir in) with eggs, oil and vanilla just enough to blend together.
Spoon into a greased muffin pan.
Fill to the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet. Add chicken pieces, browning slowly, turning once.
Remove chicken from skillet. Cook onions and garlic in oil until tender, but not brown.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cooking wine. Return chicken to skillet and sauce mixture. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in cooking wine. Cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes more turning chicken occasionally. Serve with well buttered noodles or spaghetti sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: honey milk balls
directions: Mix well.
Shape into balls.
(Can leave plain or roll in nuts or coconut.)

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix the cream cheese, onions, corned beef and black olives together.
Chill overnight.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Put flour and brown sugars in bowl and mix.
Cut shortening in.
Add oats and mix well.
Spread half the crumb mixture in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour cherry filling on mixture and sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs and add to mixture. Add pineapple and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix chicken, soup, broth, peas, carrots and add to margarine.
Mix Bisquick and milk. Pour over top of casserole. Bake 25 minutes at 425° or until done.

title: jello dessert salad
directions: Mix and congeal Jell-O and pineapple. Blend and spread Dream Whip and cream cheese on hardened Jell-O.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt
all ingredients except peanuts and soda.
When it comes to
a boil, add the peanuts and cook until the syrup is light brown.
Add
soda
and
mix well.
Pour on cookie sheet (well-greased).
When cool, break into pieces.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Mix eggs, garlic powder, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Spread mixture on rolled out dough.
Put pepperoni and cheese on (cut pepperoni and Provolone cheese into small pieces).
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Let rise for a while.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Brush with melted butter, if you want.

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Mix all together. Coat chicken and marinate for 3 to 4 hours. Broil or barbecue for 10 to 12 minutes; baste halfway through.

title: beef summer sausage
directions: Mix well, cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Repeat for a second 24 hours.
Form into 5 rolls.
Bake on a rack at 180 degrees for 5 hours in broiler pan.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into strips, spray pan with Pam.
Brown chicken. Sprinkle about 3 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce on meat.
Put vegetables into pan.
Cook a few minutes, barely let them get done. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium-high heat, keep stirred.

title: party punch
directions: Let stand 10 minutes; stir.

title: friendship cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and dry ingredients.
Fold in fruits and nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube or loaf pan at 350°.

title: lemon beans and mushrooms
directions: Place beans in boiling, salted water.
Cook for 10 minutes. Cool beans under cold water; drain and set aside.
Heat butter in frying pan.
Add mushrooms and cook 2 to 3 minutes over high heat. Do not stir.
Season generously with salt and pepper.
Mix well. Cook for 2 minutes.
Add beans, lemon rind and juice; cover and cook 3 minutes.
Serve.

title: hot ketchup
directions: Boil together the first 3 ingredients until done.
Drain in bag 1 hour or longer, then put through squeezer-strainer to remove seeds and skin.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook hard for 10 minutes, then can.

title: lentil soup
directions: This recipe can be altered to accommodate your family's tastes.
Just substitute your
favorite
vegetables for any of those in the recipe.

title: peach pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add milk and melted butter. Pour over peaches and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow roll
directions: Save out 1 cup of crushed graham crackers.
Mix all the remaining ingredients.
Put wax paper on table.
Sprinkle with extra cup of crackers.
Form mixture into a log.
Wrap up in wax paper and then a damp cloth.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Slice to serve; top with cream.
Delicious!

title: apple harvest blondies
directions: Place cream cheese in freezer 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in saucepan. Remove from burner and stir in 2 cups brown sugar. Add eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Fold in chopped apple. Place in ungreased (or sprayed) 13 x 9 pan. Chop cream cheese in small pieces and mix with remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over batter and bake 35 minutes. Serve warm or at room temperature. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and curry powder together and add to lima beans and bacon.
Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: whopper cookies
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Blend in sugars, eggs and peanut butter; mix until smooth.
Add oats, baking soda, raisins and chocolate chips.
(Dough will be sticky.) Drop on a greased baking sheet with a large spoon or ice cream scoop.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove cookies to a wire rack to cool.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: shrimp magnifico
directions: In buttered skillet, heat shrimp and garlic.
Add salt and pepper.
Remove with a slotted spatula to a shallow baking dish. Mix flour with a little white wine and add to the butter in skillet, stirring until golden.
Stir in oregano, rest of wine and olive oil, cooking until a little thickened.
Pour over shrimp. Combine cheese, parsley and crumbs; sprinkle over shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: quick salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 30 minutes and enjoy with tortilla chips.

title: egg kisses
directions: In small bowl, beat egg whites, vanilla, cream of tartar and salt to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, beating until very stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved.
Bake at 275° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Heat sugar and both syrups until boiling; remove from heat. Add peanut butter, then corn flakes and peanuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted chocolate chips.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: breakfast monkey bread
directions: Cut
biscuits
into
Put	sugar
and
teaspoon cinnamon into
bowl.
Roll	biscuits
(save mixture), then put into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.	Mix butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in boiler.
Add enough
sugar	to saved mixture to make 1 cup. Add to boiler and	bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tasty instant s-f cocoa mix(sugar free)
directions: Stir together milk powder, nondairy creamer, cocoa powder, Equal and, if desired, cinnamon.
Cover and store in an airtight container.
For each serving, in a heat-proof mug, add 3/4 cup boiling water to 1/3 cup cocoa mix, stir to dissolve.
Makes 2 2/3 cups mix.
(Enough for 8 (6 ounce) servings.) 104 calories per serving.
Diabetic exchange - 1 milk.

title: frosted chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in large bowl; mix well. Combine 2 sticks margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Pour into flour mixture; mix well. Add mixture of buttermilk and soda; mix well. Add eggs, 2 teaspoons vanilla and cinnamon; mix well. Pour into greased 11 x 15-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until a drop forms a firm ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts if desired and beat until stiff.
Spread in buttered 11 x 7-inch pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli cornbread(even folks who "hate" broccoli will like this cornbread!)
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan or iron skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients and then add melted margarine.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is so moist, it doesn't need to be buttered when you eat it.

title: rum cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and rum. Add egg yolks, milk and dry ingredients.
Stiffly beat egg whites. Add to mixture by folding in.
Bake in greased and floured 9-inch tube pan 1 hour at 375°.
After cake is cool, paint with Rum Sauce.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, rice, pudding mix, raisins and egg in saucepan. Stir over heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Makes 10 servings.

title: katie's mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, salt and pepper; drain.
In large saucepan, combine enchilada sauce, soups, chillies and milk. Bring to a boil.
Layer crushed chips, meat and sauce mix. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake or microwave until cheese melts.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: pecan sandies cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar and baking soda.
Mix for 15 minutes with the mixer.
Add flour and nuts. Drop by small teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Cut each squash into 4 or 5 crosswise slices; remove seeds.
Arrange 3 chops on bottom of crock-pot.
Place all squash slices on top, then add the last 3 chops.
Combine salt, pepper, sugar, Kitchen Bouquet, orange juice and peel.
Cover; cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: sunday fried chicken
directions: Coat chicken with combined flour and seasoning.
Brown on all sides in hot Crisco.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, for about 45 minutes until the chicken is tender or put in oven for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Mix together flour, pecans and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add whipped topping.
Spread over cooled flour crust.
Whip together 3 cups milk and butterscotch pudding mix until thick.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
You may top with whipped topping if you wish.
Other puddings may also be used.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix well.
Put in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours to congeal.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Bring Karo to boil.
Pour over coconut.
Mix well with fork. Let sit 2 hours.
Shape into whatever color wafers you desire.

title: salsa dempsey
directions: Cut onion in half and quarter tomatoes.
Place in a food processor or blender with all other ingredients.
Blend until mixture is all finely minced.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Salt and pepper the pork chops and brown in the oil.
Remove pork chops from pan and set aside.
Pour rice into the drippings in skillet and cook, stirring constantly until light brown.
In a large casserole, place rice and add remaining ingredients.
Lay pork chops on top, cover and cook for 1 hour at 350° or until liquid is absorbed.

title: fried apples
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add apple slices.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over apples.
Cover and cook over medium heat. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
When apples are soft, remove from pan and serve.

title: spiced sausage
directions: Add to the chili mixture as many smoked sausages as desired. Simmer on low heat 30 minutes.

title: golden nugget cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Roll balls in mixture.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Add to others.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat 4 Tbsp. of oil in a pan.
Pour in the beaten onion and eggs and stir fry quickly.
When the eggs are in tiny pieces, remove them from heat.

title: my red velvet cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a 2-quart mixing bowl.
Mix good.
Make well in center.
Add all the other ingredients.
Mix good with electric mixer.
Bake in three 9-inch cake plates at 350°.

title: coloring macaroni and rice
directions: Mix together in small bowl and place macaroni/rice in mixture until it reaches the desired shade.
Dry on waxed paper.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend Crisco and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add with milk, vanilla and lemon extract to shortening-sugar mix. Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Put batter in pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle cake with powdered sugar.

title: pound cake with seven minute frosting
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour and milk (alternate), adding flour last.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a 300° preheated oven for 2 hours.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Put in saucepan the water, cocoa, shortening and oleo.
Bring to boil and add to flour and sugar.
Mix together eggs, soda, cinnamon and buttermilk.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: southern pecan bars
directions: Sift 1 1/3 cups flour with baking powder.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Blend in flour mixture; stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Press mixture firmly into greased 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salt water until tender.
Remove bones and cut into pieces.
Spread pieces in Pyrex dish.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Spread stuffing over the soup mixture.
Put margarine in broth and let melt.
Pour over the stuffing.
Be sure all of stuffing is covered.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy apples
directions: In a small baking dish, melt 1/2 stick margarine (be melted in microwave).
Empty can of apples in dish.
Mix brown sugar, nuts, flour and oleo until crumbly.
Put on top of apples and bake for 30 minutes.

title: crustless egg pie
directions: Blend all
ingredients	and pour into a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Serve in round mountain bread.
Use bread and crackers to dip.

title: sausage with potatoes and cabbage
directions: Place sausage in skillet.
Layer onion over sausage.
Next, spread potatoes and top with cabbage.
Cover and cook over very low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir gently every 30 minutes, trying to keep the cabbage on top.
If this is steamed cooked, it should not need any water; however, if it starts browning, add a little water and turn down the heat.

title: ready in a minute
directions: Grate Mozzarella cheese in bowl.
Add mayonnaise.
Sprinkle in onion, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Add chili peppers. Mix well.
Bake in baking dish until bubbly at 350°.
Serve hot with Triscuits or other crackers.
Delicious!!

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spread sour cream on meat mixture and top with cheese.
Unroll crescent rolls and place on top of cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese vegetable soup
directions: Cook vegetables in 1 cup water as directed.
Take vegetables out of water, saving the water and adding enough water to make 2 cups.
Add 2 chicken bouillon cubes and heat until dissolved. Saute onion in butter.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add the milk to the water mixture.
Add the onion, butter and flour mixture to the milk.
Stir and heat until mixture is smooth.
Add shredded cheese and heat until melted.
Chop the cooled vegetables and add to mixture.
Heat to serve.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in margarine until crumble. Add egg, orange peel and juice all at once.
Stir until evenly moist.
Fold in raisins and cranberries.
Place in greased and lightly floured loaf pan.
Bake 350° for 1 hour, 10 minutes.
You may substitute cranberries for the raisins, using a total of 3 c. cranberries.

title: viva italian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Viva Italian salad dressing for 1 hour minimum in a tinfoil lined baking dish.
Roll chicken in the mixture of Parmesan cheese and Rice Krispies.
Place chicken back into Viva Italian salad dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frosty cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice; add water to make 2 cups. Bring to boil; dissolve Jell-O in it.
Chill until partially set. Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Fold into Cool Whip, then fold into Jell-O and fruits.
Pour in 3-quart Pyrex pan or individual molds.
Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: ham cheese omelet
directions: Mix together cream cheese, ham, chives and mushrooms.
Combine eggs with milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Beat until foamy.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cover noodles with cold water.
Cook and stir beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown. Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and mushrooms and heat to boiling. Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients. Drain noodles.
Spread 3 tablespoons of the cheese mixture to edges of 1 noodle.
Roll up; cut roll into halves.
Repeat with other noodles.
Place rolls, cut side down, in beef mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir together thoroughly flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda. Combine strawberry jam and sour cream.
Add jam mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in walnuts.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix chicken, onion, both soups, sour cream and chili peppers together.
Roll up in corn tortilla. Place in a well-greased casserole dish.
Cover with Cheddar and Monterey Jack grated cheese and the rest of the mix and bake about 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges and add to the pudding mix and Tang.
Stir until thickened.
Add fruit and chill overnight.
Add bananas before serving.
Sprinkle top of salad with poppy seed.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes.
Remove water and peel potatoes.
Slice potatoes lengthwise in a baking dish.
Spread potatoes on the bottom of dish.
Sprinkle sugar, brown sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon on potatoes.
Layer potatoes and repeat seasoning process.
On the top layer, chop 2 tablespoons of butter.
Spread canned milk over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves approximately 15 to 20.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well and keep in an airtight container. Use 3-4 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9-inch Bundt pan. Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Stir to blend. Pour or spoon into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack for 20 minutes.
Turn out of pan and cool completely before storing.

title: hot dried beef dip
directions: Mix all together and place in ovenproof dish.
Cover top with chopped pecans.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve with small rye bread or crackers.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread into a 9-inch square pan.

title: cran-orange-apple pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt; add 1 tablespoon of water at a time, mixing with a fork until it reaches the desired consistency.
Divide dough in half and form 2 balls.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Place 1 tortilla on a microwave-safe plate.
Layer with half of the pepperoni, tomatoes, salsa, olives and cheese.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top with half of the lettuce.
Make a second pizza with remaining ingredients.

title: chicken cheese strata
directions: Cut bread into bite-size cubes.
Place in bottom of two 5 x 5 x 1 1/2-inch baking dishes.
Cut up soup noodles.
In medium bowl, combine soup, noodles and eggs.
Pour over bread cubes.
Cook at Medium-high or Power 7 (7%) for 5 minutes.
Top with cheese. Cover; cook at Medium-high or Power 7 (7%) for 1 minute, until nearly set.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: real easy corn soup
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers in oil until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Add tomato sauce, Ro-Tel and cook on low heat for about 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add drained whole kernel corn and smother for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add creamed corn to pot. Cook on low to medium heat for about 1 hour.
Add corn-on-the-cob and cook for 15 to 20 minutes more.
Make sure you have enough water at all times.
Use 2 cups of water to every can of corn to be on the safe side.
Thicken with flour.
Leftovers can be frozen.

title: best cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots, bell pepper and onions together.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix together sugar, lemon juice and mayonnaise. Add to cabbage mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: sausage balls and barbecue sauce
directions: Cook above for 30 minutes; pour over meatballs.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow mixing instructions for any basic fruit cake.
Bake in a very slow oven (275°) for 3 to 4 hours.
Test with toothpick before removing from oven.

title: carrot pie
directions: Beat together cooked carrots, egg, salt, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and milk smooth, using mixer, food processor or blender. Pour into pie shell and bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 50 minutes or until filling is firm.
Cool on rack. Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times. Combine oil, milk, and coffee; add to dry ingredients at one time. Mix at medium speed for 2 min. Add eggs and vanilla extract; beat 2 more min. Batter will be thin. Pour into two greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 325° for 25-30 min. Cool cake 15 min before removing from pan. cool completely and frost with your favorite white frosting. 8 to 10 servings.

title: bistecca alla florentina
directions: In an 11 x 7-inch baking dish, combine first 5 ingredients. Add steak and pierce deeply with a fork.
Cover and marinate overnight.
Remove steak and side aside.
In a saucepan, heat remaining marinade.
Basting and turning frequently, grill 4 to 5-inches from heat, about 30 minutes for medium.
Serve steak with sauce.
Garnish with mushrooms and anchovies.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream together the wet ingredients, then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Do not chill.
Place in cookie press.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes about 100 to 125 cookies.

title: southern brunswick stew
directions: In 4-quart pan, add all ingredients.
Heat on medium temperature to serving temperature.
Good with southern cornbread!

title: caramels
directions: Combine the ingredients and cook slowly until candy thermometer reads 240°.
Put on buttered broiler pan and let set overnight.
Cut into squares and wrap in wax paper.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cook 5 minutes.
Take mixture off stove and add cream cheese; let melt into sauce.
Dip with large Fritos chips.

title: ranch style chicken with noodles
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add vegetables.

title: fat-free devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 9-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at medium, beat egg whites, light brown sugar and buttermilk 2 minutes until blended.
Add flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, grated peel and vanilla extract.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan; bake 25 to 30 minutes until pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes in pan on wire rack.
Remove cake from pan to wire rack and cool completely, about 30 minutes.
Garnish.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix meal and flour in a bowl.
Add egg and milk; mix this all together and add oil.
Pour in baking dish or pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes in a preheated 450° oven.
Bake in 10-inch skillet for thin corn bread or smaller skillet for thicker bread.

title: corn chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt oleo and cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: jerky
directions: Cover meat with sauce made of remaining ingredients. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Drain and place strips on a rack over a shallow pan or broiler.
Bake at 150° for 8 to 10 hours until dried.
Cool and eat or store in a tightly covered container.
If the jerky is to be eaten right away, 8 hours of drying time should be sufficient and will make chewing easier for young children.

title: shrimp creole #2
directions: In skillet, mix shortening and flour.
Make sure all lumps of flour are dissolved.
Mix in all spices and saute (do not brown spices).
Add tomatoes.
Add enough water to make gravy.
Simmer for 45 minutes with shrimp in gravy.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix
sugar and flour in heavy saucepan.
Stir in Seven-Up. Heat,
stirring
constantly,
until
mixture is thick and clear. Stir in jello.
Cool.
Pour over berries in shell.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add onions and peppers.
Mix together remaining ingredients; add and cover.
Cook for 1 hour.
Serve over rice, spaghetti or noodles sprinkled with grated cheese.

title: apple crunch
directions: In mixing bowl, work butter until creamy.
Add sugar and work until smooth.
Beat eggs slightly and stir in.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together and stir until batter is smooth.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Peel apples and slice into 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Spread batter over apples and bake 10 minutes.
Turn oven temperature down to 350° and bake 20 minutes or until apples are tender (test with toothpick). Serve warm or cold, plain or with cream, whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: night-before french toast
directions: Arrange bread in well-buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine next 5 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Pour over bread.
Chill, covered, for 4 to 36 hours.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve with syrup, honey, fruit-flavored yogurt, or fresh fruit.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put half of bread in baking dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients; put half on top of bread cubes.
Repeat.
Beat eggs, add milk and salt. Pour over mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add 1 cup mushroom soup, slightly diluted, over top when ready to cook.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese last 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add pumpkin, vanilla and water; mix thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture and blend well. Stir in pecans and dates.
Bake in 4 greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: diabetic chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, stir in cocoa, milk, eggs and sugar substitute with flour or cornstarch. After it thickens, add butter.

title: crunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cereal and cinnamon.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package except fold cereal mixture into batter. Pour into ungreased 12-cup Bundt cake pan. Bake and cool as directed.
Serve with fresh fruit, if desired.
tags: one-step white angel food cake mix

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk.
In shallow casserole, arrange vegetable and chicken with rice in layers.
Top with soup mixture and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, covered.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cut on stove to 250°.
Put cake mix in the bowl.
Put water in and eggs.
Stir until it is kind of thick, then put the peanut butter in and stir together.
Get your spoon and put a little cookie dough on it. Put a little on the pan, but first put Pam on the pan.
Let them cook about 25 minutes.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until soft.
Add crawfish and Ro-Tel tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Soak bread in water and squeeze, then add to mixture.
Add cooked rice and parsley; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Cut in shortening. Add egg and bananas, oatmeal and nuts. Beat until thoroughly blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done. Makes 3 1/2 doz.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and diced chicken.
Pour into 9 x 13 casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, until bubbly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix well; chill before serving.

title: zesty meatball appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.

title: may's aubergine-eggplant with mustard seed and yogurt
directions: Peel and dice eggplant in 1-inch cubes.
Grind mustard seed in coffee grinder.
Add cayenne and 1 cup water.
Mix and set aside.

title: holly potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, in a bag.
Slice potatoes and shake in the bag until covered.
Melt butter and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mom's favorite chop suey
directions: Fry hamburger.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
Add onions, celery and bean sprouts to meat, cooked not too soft.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Put the ingredients for dressing in container with tightly covered lid; shake until sugar dissolves.
Pour over salad just before serving so noodles will stay crisp.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Scatter rice in dish.
Place chicken over rice, salt and pepper to taste.
In mixing bowl, mix cream of chicken soup with water and pour over rice and chicken.
Sprinkle dry soup over top.
Cover with foil and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours in preheated oven.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients, reserving juice.
Set aside. Combine next 3 ingredients in medium saucepan; stir well.
Add reserved fruit juices and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Combine reserved fruit with cherries and bananas in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour cornstarch mixture over fruit.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: date nut ball
directions: Cook butter and dates on low heat until dates dissolve.
Add sugar and eggs; cook 10 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, cereal and nuts.
Cool.
Make into balls and dip into coconut.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Cook
until
tender
the
potatoes
and onion in enough water to cover.
In another pot, do the same with the carrots and celery.
Combine the 2 pots (including water).

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain.
Cream shortening with sugar, then add beaten egg and milk.
Add oatmeal and raisins; mix well.
Add flour, sifted with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop onto greased pans and bake 12 minutes in moderate oven (350° to 325°).
Makes 3 dozen medium sized cookies.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into electric ice cream freezer. Put in salt and ice.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine oil and warm milk.
Add milk mixture along with the yeast to dry ingredients.
Mix well by hand or dough hook.
If by hand, knead 5 to 7 minutes.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick on floured board surface.
Cut with a small biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter.
Stack one on top of the other, forming one biscuit.
Let rise 1 hour and bake at 425° until brown.
Use large size cutter to make hamburger buns.

title: tor teri's
directions: Soften cream cheese so it is easy to blend (can put in microwave for few minutes if short on time).
Chop or dice bell peppers and onions; fold into the cream cheese.
Mix and add salsa and cumin; mix well.
(Taste; if it needs more salsa and cumin, add to your liking.)
Take the mixture and spoon it onto a tortilla shell.
Smooth it out; try to get it as even as you can. I usually spread it over 2/3 of the shell, because when you "roll" it, it will come out the other end.

title: chocolate kiss-peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Beat butter and peanut butter until well blended.
Add granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture until well combined. Using a level tablespoonful for each, shape into balls.
Roll each ball in granulated sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Press an unwrapped chocolate Kiss on top of each.
Bake 2 minutes longer. Cool.

title: brown rice(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake covered 1 hour at 350°.
Recipe can be halved.

title: marie winkler's homemade bread
directions: In a large bowl mix 2 pints water, dry milk, margarine, salt and sugar.
Add 3 to 4 cups of flour.
Mix yeast in 1 pint of water as per directions on yeast package.
Add to mixture.
Gradually stir in the rest of the flour.
Knead on floured surface 10 to 15 minutes.
Place dough in large greased pan.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Turn out on floured surface and shape into 5 or 6 medium loaves.
Place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Three cups wheat flour can be substituted for 3 cups of the white flour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice the apples and place in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle 1 cup sugar onto apples.
Mix in separate bowl, softened margarine, flour, brown sugar and oats.
Then place mixture on the apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with dressing; place layer of dressing in bottom of baking dish, then layer of chicken.
To each can of soup, add 1/2 can of water and mix.
Pour over chicken layer.
Top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach leaves into bite-sized pieces after thick stems and veins are removed and spinach has been washed and thoroughly dried.
Add remaining ingredients and toss with dressing of choice.

title: squash bake
directions: Combine vegetables and basil in a 1 3/4-quart casserole dish coated with cooking spray.
Toss lightly.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: top secret orange julius
directions: Combine all of the ingredients, except ice, in a blender and blend on high speed for 15 to 30 seconds or until the sugar is dissolved. Add the ice and blend for another 10 to 15 seconds or so, until ice is mostly crushed yet still a bit coarse. Makes 2 (16-ounce) drinks.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve as dip for raw vegetables.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add reserved pineapple juice to vanilla pudding.
Stir in fruits and nuts.
Chill.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Grease a 3-quart rectangular casserole dish.
Mix together chicken, macaroni, soup, milk, eggs, onion and cheese.
Transfer to casserole. Cover with foil. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 1/2 hours before cooking. Stir melted butter into stuffing mix. Spread on top of casserole. Cover with foil. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans and parsley. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chicken nugget casserole
directions: Place chicken nuggets in 11 by 9 baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, top with spaghetti sauce, mozzarella cheese and Italian seasoning.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes, yields 4-6 servings.

title: crab meat ball
directions: Blend all together. Shape into a ball and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice in a mixing bowl.
Blend in pineapple, then whipped cream and nuts.
Mix well and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Freeze.

title: jane's mayonnaise
directions: Combine and
beat
with
electric
mixer the egg yolks, salt and vinegar
in
deep
bowl.
Squeeze lemons.
Then begin adding 1/4 to 1/2	cup oil to egg mixture.
Then alternate oil and lemon juice until all has been used.
Makes full quart.

title: easy coffee cake with fruit topping
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter, baking powder and salt together; reserve 1/2 cup of mixture for topping.
Beat together eggs and milk; add to other mixture and stir together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour canned pie filling (such as cherry, strawberry, etc.) on top.
Take 1/2 cup of the crumb mixture and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: vermont apple slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve in cabbage leaf-lined bowl and top with apple slices.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Blend together cream cheese and French vanilla pudding.
Add powdered sugar and milk.
Mix well until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with reserved 1/2 cup Oreo crumbs and chill.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and peanut butter. Add sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Shape into balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Top with chocolate kisses and bake 5 minutes more.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Use on spinach, orange sections and slivered almonds.

title: mystery cake
directions: Rinse sauerkraut thoroughly; cut up into small pieces.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cocoa. Add to creamed mixture alternately with water, beating after each addition.
Stir in sauerkraut and nuts.
Turn into greased and floured pans (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Frost with sour cream frosting.

title: super bowl oyster crackers
directions: Toss together in large bowl and serve. Also freezes well.

title: caramel fudge brownies
directions: Melt caramels, 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and Eagle Brand milk over low heat (preferably in double boiler); set aside.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, 3/4 cup margarine or butter, milk and nuts and mix.
Press half of the mixture into the pan and reserve remainder for the top.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: five-minute chocolate cake
directions: Always start with dry ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch round pans, three 8-inch round pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for round pans, 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from pans; cool completely.
Frost cooled cake.

title: chunky steak with rice
directions: In a saucepan, mix soup, peas and carrots over medium heat. Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2.

title: lentil chili
directions: Saute garlic, onions and hot pepper in olive oil.
Add lentils, water and spices.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes in a covered pot until lentils are tender.
Add tomato paste, juice, vinegar, sugar, red or green pepper and celery.
Add salt and additional water, if needed.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Serve plain, over rice or pasta.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Meanwhile, fry 1 pound bacon until crisp.
Last 10 minutes of baking time, add bacon bits.

title: summer dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover; stir and brown slightly uncovered. Serve warm.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Roll in slices of ham.
Chill before slicing.
Good on sesame crackers.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine the ground beef, eggs, cracker crumbs, onion, Tabasco sauce, garlic salt and salt.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Combine the catsup, water, vinegar, brown sugar, onion, mustard, salt and sauces; pour over the meatballs.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: candy crunch
directions: Line 15 x 10 baking pan with foil. Place pretzels in large bowl. In large saucepan over medium heat, heat condensed milk until warm (about 5 minutes). Remove from heat and immediately stir in white baking pieces until melted. Pour over pretzels, stirring to coat. Immediately spread mixture into prepared pan. Sprinkle with dried fruit. Press down lightly with back of spoon. Chill 1 to 2 hours. Break into chunks. Store loosely covered at room temperature. Makes about 1 3/4 pounds.

title: 4 salisbury steaks
directions: Shape into oval patties and fry in 1 tablespoon oil.
To make the gravy, remove the meat from the pan and add 1/4 pound fresh mushrooms to the drippings.
In a small bowl, stir 3 tablespoons flour, adding 1 1/2 cups water, a little bit at a time.
Add this to the mushrooms with 1 tablespoon catsup and 1 teaspoon salt. Serve this with mashed potatoes, a salad and warm bread and you have a very nice meal for 4 people.

title: stuffed date drops
directions: Cut pecans or walnuts lengthwise.
Stuff dates with nuts; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and soda; set aside.
In a mixer bowl, beat brown sugar and margarine with electric mixer on medium speed until combined.
Add egg yolk and beat on medium speed until combined.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately, beating on low speed until combined.
Stir in filled dates.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls (1 date per cookie) onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 7 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove, cool.
Frost with Golden Frosting.
Makes 24.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Mix with cornbread crumbs.
Stir in onion.
Mix well.
Add eggs.
Mix, then add soup. Bake in greased casserole dish or favorite pan in a 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls no. 2
directions: Blend sugar, oleo and peanut butter.
Roll in balls and chill until
firm.
Melt
butterscotch
chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in melted mixture and place on waxed paper to cool.
May be stored in airtight container or frozen.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into balls about the size of a large walnut.
Arrange in flat baking pans, one layer to a pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cake coolies
directions: Mix together.
Pat evenly in a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: squash puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls approximately the size of hush puppies into hot, deep oil; drain.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Boil and peel potatoes.
Warm mushroom soup; add butter and chopped onions and cheese; mix.
Add sour cream.
Put in baking dish; dot with butter and sprinkle with crushed corn flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: venison chili
directions: In a large, heavy pot or Dutch oven, heat oil.
Add meat and stir until lightly browned.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add tomato paste, tomatoes, beer, cumin, chili powder, paprika, oregano, salt, peppers, salsa, bouillon cubes and cocoa.
Simmer over low heat about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
One half hour before end of cooking time, add drained beans. Serve with grated cheese sprinkled on top. Makes about 10 servings.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Pour small amount of oil in skillet. Add flour as needed and slowly brown.
Add salt and pepper, then add milk.
Simmer until it starts to thicken. Add tomatoes and simmer until it thickens.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly over greased pan.
Combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Evenly spoon batter over coconut and pecans.
In large bowl, combine confectioners sugar, margarine and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Spoon evenly over batter.
Bake at 375° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: beefed up biscuit casserole
directions: In large frypan, brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Pull apart each biscuit into 2 layers.
Place 10 biscuit layers over bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine 1/2 cup of cheese, milk and egg; mix well.
Remove meat mixture from heat; stir in milk mixture.
Spoon over dough.
Arrange remaining biscuit layers on top.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple-citrus punch
directions: Mix juices and carbonated beverage in large punch bowl.
Spoon scoop of sherbet into bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Wash and chop broccoli.
Crumble bacon; mix with broccoli, onion and walnuts.

title: polka dot cake
directions: Mix chopped dates and hot water; set aside to cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put first 6 ingredients, except peanut butter, in double boiler.
Stir until smooth.
Then add peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Pour in pan, cool and cut.

title: one big cookie(lo-cal)
directions: Mix well; spread on cookie sheet to desired thickness and bake at 350° for only 5 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; mix well.
Pour into 9-inch buttered pie pan.
Makes its own crust, filling and topping!
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Like a custard.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds, lemon juice and mayonnaise. Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: cauliflower soup (weight watchers)
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onion.
Add cauliflower and broth; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 12 to 15 minutes. Combine milk and flour smoothly.
Add to saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until thickened and boils.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, stirring, until melted.
Add salt and pepper.
(See Trudy Priede's recipe for the "fat" version.)

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fry by tablespoon in deep fat.

title: squash hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion, buttermilk and eggs.
Stir in squash.
Drop by teaspoon into hot, deep fat.
This makes a lot of hush puppies.
The recipe would be easy to halve.

title: taco soup(lighter eating - 2 points per cup)
directions: Brown meat and onions, drain. Mix dressing mix and taco seasoning mixes in to meat. Then, without draining, add all of the other ingredients. Simmer 1 hour. If you can find the reduced sodium taco seasoning and the reduced sodium Hidden Valley it is very helpful because of the high sodium count in both seasonings and the chili hot beans. This is delicious served with Baked tostitos chips. (They aren't in the point count per cup serving.)

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Cook cabbage in water in a large pot.
Brown ground beef.
I always put my onion and bell pepper in with my meat when browning. Pour beef mixture into cabbage.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
I think it is better if you add a little red hot pepper of some type.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove skin from chicken parts. Combine in a plastic bag the wheat germ, cornmeal and your choice of seasonings.
Dip chicken parts in the low-fat milk, then shake the chicken parts, one at a time, in the bag containing the wheat germ/cornmeal mix.
Re-dip the coated pieces in milk and shake again in the mixture.
Bake chicken pieces on a lightly oiled cookie sheet for 25 minutes.
Turn pieces over and bake for 20 minutes more.

title: eizzie's dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and biscuits in large bowl.
Add chopped onions, salt and pepper.
Add broth; mix until the consistency of cornbread, maybe a little soupy.
Cook in shallow broiling pans (2) at 400° until tops are golden brown.
Will serve large family!

title: pickled fish
directions: Fillet Northern and cut in 3/4-inch pieces.
Soak in salt water (1 cup of salt to 6 cups of water) for 24 hours.
Drain. Cover with white vinegar for 24 hours.
Drain.

title: campfire fry biscuits
directions: Heat 3 to 4 inches of oil in a frying pan.
Place biscuit dough into hot oil.
Brown and serve.

title: crispy oven baked blackened fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all dry ingredients, except fish seasoning and lemon pepper, in bowl.
Spray cookie sheet with oil, 3 sprays; dip fillets in cornmeal mix.
Shake off excess and place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle seasoning and pepper on both sides of fillets.
Spray top of fillets with oil.
Bake on lower oven rack for 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° after 25 minutes and bake for 10 additional minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour equally into three 1-quart containers.
Finish filling with water.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 2 hours before serving.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine	and
add
brown
sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add	flour, one cup at a time, mixing well after each cup.
Add chocolate chips;
mix well.	Add nuts, if desired, and mix
well.
Spread into greased 11 x 16-inch pan. Bake at 325° for
to
minutes.
Cool until able to cut easily and place on plate.

title: chicken marbella
directions: In a large sealable bowl (to keep your refrigerator from reeking), combine chicken quarters, garlic, oregano, pepper, salt, vinegar, olive oil, prunes, olives, capers and juice and bay leaves.
Cover and let marinate overnight in the refrigerator. (Note:
The chicken must be marinated overnight to blend the flavors and to keep the chicken moist.)
Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange chicken in a single layer in one or two large, shallow baking pans and spoon marinade over it evenly.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with brown sugar and pour white wine around them.
Bake for 50 minutes to an hour, basting frequently with pan juices.
Chicken is done when thigh pieces pricked with a fork at their thickest, yield clear yellow (rather than pink) juice.
With a slotted spoon, transfer chicken, prunes, olives and capers to a serving platter. Moisten with a few spoonfuls of pan juices and sprinkle generously with parsley.
Pass remaining pan juices in a sauceboat.

title: russian tea cake
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup powdered sugar until smooth.
Grate pecans until very fine.
Add flour and pecans to creamed mixture and mix just until blended.
Add vanilla and blend.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook, drain and arrange broccoli in greased baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: meat puffs with mushroom gravy
directions: Combine first six ingredients with a fork.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Heat oil in skillet over moderately high heat.
Brown meatballs, drain the skillet.
Add mushroom soup and water combination and simmer on low heat 20 to 25 minutes.
Cheap and delicious!

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken after slicing it into small pieces.
Add onions, salt, pepper, taco sauce and water.
Heat sauce and chicken soup. Dip tortillas in hot sauce.
Place 2 tablespoons meat mixture and a little cheese in tortilla.
Roll up and put in baking dish. Cover the rolled up tortillas with remaining hot sauce; sprinkle with remaining cheese over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 250°.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Brown onion and meats in Dutch oven or electric skillet. Cook chicken until done or use leftover turkey or chicken.
Add vegetables, tomatoes, water and spices.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until it is time to eat!
Or put in crock-pot.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil, add eggs, flour and remaining ingredients. Add apples and nuts last. Bake in a greased bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. To glaze mix 1 cup brown sugar, 1 stick margarine and 1/4 cup milk, cook until it bubbles and pour over cake.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except pie shell.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue to bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean. Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hot tamales
directions: Mix well and roll in foil.
Wrap ends well.

title: cauliflower dish for buffet
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Bring broth to boil.
Add cauliflower and cook 10 minutes.
Peel, seed and chop tomatoes.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Cook berries with all other ingredients until thickened.
Fill pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Drain and pat dry mandarin oranges.
Set aside.
Mix together sour cream, cottage cheese, Cool Whip and powdered orange gelatin. Gently fold in mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: quick onion soup for 2
directions: In a medium saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter; cook onion until tender, about 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add beef broth, Worcestershire sauce.
Cook additional 5 minutes.
Divide soup between 2 ovenproof bowls.
Top each with toasted French bread and 2 tablespoons grated Swiss cheese.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Sift cake mix and jello together.
Mix oil and water.
Add 1/2 of cake mix.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add rest of mix.
Add over 1/2 the strawberries and bake in 2 layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Measure the salt and sugar in bowl.
Soak the yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Heat the milk to scald.
Add the lard to the milk.
When melted, add to salt and sugar.
Stir in the cold water, then add the whole wheat flour.
Let stand 15 minutes or so, then add the yeast mixture and the white flour, until pretty stiff.
Knead well.
Let rise until double.
Let rise again, then roll out and put in pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's butter cookies
directions: Beat together eggs, butter and sugar.
Add baking powder.
Add flour and vanilla; mix all together.
Roll into a loaf.
Place in refrigerator until well chilled.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: chip chocolate orange chiffon cake
directions: Bake cake in layers as directed.
Spread Cider Filling (following) between cooled layers.
Frost top and sides with White Butter Icing.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese.
Whip Milnot.
Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Mix Milnot and Jell-O into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll into ball, then roll in crushed pecans.
May be frozen.

title: lisa's spaghetti
directions: Cook meat with onion.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: impossible chicken vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix chicken and other veggies into pie pan, spreading evenly over bottom.
Beat eggs and milk together, adding Bisquick, herbs and cheeses.
Whisk all together and pour over chicken mix.
Bake 35 minutes or until set.
Can make mushroom soup gravy and pour over when serving.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cover this with water and boil until tender.
Do not drain!!

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Pour applesauce in greased shallow casserole.
Crumble crackers into melted margarine.
Stir in sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle sugar mixture on applesauce.
Boil 10 minutes or bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice, until cucumbers are crisp-tender and onions are transparent.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well until smooth.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and apple pie spice.
Mix.
Fold in chopped apple.
Put spread in a loaf pan that has been sprayed with Pam or greased and floured. Dough will be very stiff.
Bake at 350 degrees for 60 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle cinnamon sugar on top prior to baking.
If you use 2 small pans, bake for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with eggs and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Put remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.
Add chopped nuts if desired.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar and blend thoroughly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and part of flour and baking soda mixed.
Beat bananas to a liquid and add quickly. With remaining flour, mix with dates and nuts and add to mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 325° in a 9 x 14-inch Pyrex or in muffin tin or in loaf pans.

title: fresh blackberry pie(dessert)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add sugar mixture to blackberries.
Toss to coat fruit.
Fill a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with berry mixture.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edge. Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes. Remove foil.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oysters and bacon
directions: Place oysters on strips of bacon and put a little mustard on each. Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Place in frypan and cook until bacon is cooked.

title: no-name rice
directions: Saute onions, peppers and mushrooms in margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour in a conventional oven or for 30 minutes in the microwave.

title: feather cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; set aside.
Put in another bowl. Beat eggs, sugar, butter or vegetable oil.
Then add dry ingredients and milk.
Put in two 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana split torte
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan to make a crust.
Set aside.
Beat butter, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy and firm.
Pour over crust.
Peel and slice bananas.
Put them in the reserved pineapple juice for a few minutes to prevent browning; drain and arrange bananas on the creamed filling.
Spread the crushed pineapple over the bananas.
Top with the whipped topping and garnish with the cherries, nuts and then drizzle with the chocolate syrup.
Chill for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: bunny's hot dog sauce
directions: Saut onion and peppers until tender. Saut ground round (mash fine).
Add all together.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine ingredients by hand in large mixing bowl until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 mins.

title: feed an army casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and bell pepper (chopped).
Saute until light brown.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add mushroom soup, chicken soup and 1 can water.
Stir all ingredients together.
Add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in a shallow casserole dish.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve (about 12 hours).

title: butterscotch banana bread
directions: In small bowl combine dry ingredients.	In a large bowl combine bananas, butter and eggs; mix until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups pecans and butterscotch morsels.
Pour equally into 2 loaf pans.
Sprinkle
2/3 cup pecans on top, if desired.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.

title: sparkling holiday punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Mix.
Stir in ginger ale just before serving.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers and butter.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber and pineapple aspic
directions: After jello dissolves in water; add pineapple juice.
Put in refrigerator and chill until slightly thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into individual salad molds and chill until firm.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. Set aside.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Cook and stir beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
Spread in plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1-inch with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and sour cream, lettuce and cheese.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add mashed bananas and well beaten egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add flour and milk alternately to first mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or stem pan at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Ice while still warm with a powdered sugar icing made with a little melted oleo or mashed bananas.

title: lattice-top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoning salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup shredded cheese and 1/2 can onions. Put in 8 x 12 baking dish. Press crescent rolls together in 2 rectangles. Cut into strips. Place on casserole to form lattice top. Bake 20 to 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake additional 3 to 5 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then stir in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder and add.
Mix in remainder of ingredients.
Mix in large bowl.
Drop by big spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Leave good space between cookies.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 87 cookies.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cooked peas (drained), bean sprouts (drained), mushrooms (drained) and water chestnuts in a 9-inch casserole dish.
Add a few tablespoons mushroom liquid or milk to soup; heat.
Add to vegetables and gently toss.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place onion rings over top.
Continue baking, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sandies
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop small spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: parmesan bread sticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut 1 loaf French bread into 5 pieces, each about 4-inches long; cut each piece lengthwise into 6 sticks. Brush outsides with margarine or butter, melted.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place sticks in ungreased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Bake until golden, about 8 minutes.
Makes 30 bread sticks.

title: fried eggs
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add eggs. When whites are set, add 1 teaspoon water.
Cover skillet; cook eggs to desired doneness (about 2 minutes for soft or 4 minutes for firm).
Makes two servings.

title: impossible breakfast pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Brown sausage, onion and peppers until done; drain.
Add salt.
Spread evenly in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake about 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
(May substitute ground beef for sausage for Impossible Cheeseburger Pie.)

title: cottage cheese cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Add cottage cheese, flour, soda, baking powder and walnuts.

title: fillets elegente
directions: Thaw fish fillets enough to separate.
Arrange in an 8 x 11-inch buttered casserole dish.
Dash with pepper and dot with margarine.
Place pieces of crab over each fillet.
Spread diluted shrimp soup over the crab and fillets.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Grated Parmesan may be used instead of shredded.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well before adding coconut.
Pie forms its own crust as it bakes.
Pour in greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, eggs and pumpkin together.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, cloves and baking powder together. Add to creamed mixture, then add water, raisins and nuts.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves.
Freezes well.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Pour melted margarine in a casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients except for 1 cup of Cheddar cheese for top of casserole.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts well.

title: crisp garlic pickles
directions: Sterilize canning jars first.
Combine cucumbers, onions, green peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice; mix thoroughly.
Let stand overnight or 3 hours; drain well.
Remove garlic cloves.
Combine ingredients; pour over cucumber mix.
Bring to boil.
Fill jars to 1/2 inch of top. Process in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Start timing when water returns to boil.
Makes 5 pints.

title: chicken and vegetables(serves 1)
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and surround with vegetables. Sprinkle with 1/2 package of chicken soup; microwave on High for 12 minutes or bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal quick pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pie plate. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix vegetables, chicken and soup in ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
tags: condensed reduced fat cream of chicken soup

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour and next four ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Stir in eggs, oil, vanilla extract, and butter extract; stir until dry ingredients are moistened - do not beat.
Fold in crushed pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9 inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire rack 20 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers, on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving; the flavors will blend and intensify upon standing.

title: raw summer squash salad
directions: Slice or chop vegetables.
Mix other ingredients and drizzle over vegetables.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in a glass container.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Drain shrimp and smash with fork.
Add softened cream cheese.
