Add all other ingredients.
You can either put this in a bowl or round into a ball and chill.
Enjoy!

title: butter & herb chicken
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°F.
Wash chicken and dry with paper towels.
If needed, trim excess fat.
Thoroughly pierce chicken all over, and add a few deeper slashes for good measure.
Place chicken in baking dish.

title: party pretzels
directions: Mix Popcorn Oil, Dressing Mix & Seasonings, Pour over pretzels in a very large bowl. Stir pretzels every half hour, four times. No need to drain or blot dry.

title: potatoes o' gratin
directions: Pour potatoes in baking bowl.
Add pepper, garlic salt and milk.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 250° for 5 to 8 minutes until cheese melts.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix (spoon stir) Eagle Brand milk with 1/2 cup lemon juice. Add a dab of lemon extract.
Separate 3 egg yolks from egg whites. Put egg yellows in Eagle Brand milk mixture.

title: wild rice with mushrooms
directions: Brown chopped celery, green pepper and onion in margarine. Add mushrooms and their liquid.
Combine with cooked rice; season to taste.
Bake in greased baking dish at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: hop scotch cookies
directions: Melt morsels in microwave.
Do not overheat.
Stir in peanut butter and pour in noodles and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper and refrigerate.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together.
Put Rice Krispies into a bowl.
Pour peanut butter mixture over Krispies; mix.
Add sugar; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls; place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Put in fridge (2 hours).
Melt chocolate and wax in a double boiler and dip the balls.

title: icebox cake
directions: Follow package directions for cooking puddings in separate pans.
In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan put 1 layer of graham crackers on bottom.
Pour either pudding over that, then a layer of crackers, then a layer of pudding.
Repeat the layers until the pudding is gone.
Crush remaining crackers and sprinkle over top.
Chill 2 hours.

title: donna's lasagne
directions: In large kettle, mix tomato puree, tomato paste, water, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper.
Let simmer.

title: chocolate pudding and pie filling
directions: Cook over medium heat in a saucepan the egg yolks and milk to make a paste.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring constantly until desired consistency.

title: argentinean beef saute
directions: In large heavy skillet over medium heat, brown beef. Add onions and green pepper. Saute until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, gradually adding 1/4 cup bean liquid.
Stir occasionally about 10 minutes or until flavors blend.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple-cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce, add crushed pineapple, sour cream and nuts; pour into dish and chill.

title: potato gunk
directions: Melt 1/2 margarine in saucepan; add corn flake crumbs. Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients (potatoes can still be frozen). Pour into a greased round casserole dish and top with buttered corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1
to 1 1/2 hours.
If flat square pan is used it usually only takes 1 hour.

title: heath bar crunch trifle
directions: Crumble half of the pound cake into a large glass dish; layer half of the pudding on top, then 1/3 of the Heath bars and half of the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers (pound cake, pudding, Heath bars and Cool Whip).
Top off with the remaining 1/3 Heath bars.

title: pasta with broccoli and tuna
directions: Cut and cook broccoli; drain.
Cook pasta until tender. Drain.
Do not drain tuna.
In a saucepan put tuna in its oil with garlic for about 1 minute.
Add spices.
Add chicken broth and bring to simmer.
Add broccoli and tuna mixture to pasta; cook until heated through.
Toss in capers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Roll into balls.
Bake approximately 12 minutes or until brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Dice tomato, onion and bell pepper; mix together with meat mixture.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and Velveeta. Heat until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut or pecan brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish, stir together syrup, sugar, raw peanuts or pecans and salt.
Microwave at High power for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 minutes more.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup mixture, blending well.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy. Pour onto sheet of aluminum foil.
Let cool for 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine tuna or shrimp, yogurt, cucumber, carrot, salad dressing, dill weed, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Toss with pasta. Cover and chill for 4 to 24 hours.
Cut out 1/2 in of the core from each tomato.
Invert tomatoes.
For each, cut from top to bottom, but not quite through the stem end.
Makes 6 wedges.
Spread wedges and fill with mixture.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour butter and milk over rice.
Mix soups and pour over rice.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek!!

title: mushroom-egg-onion bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a shallow 1-quart baking dish. Heat oil in medium skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Set aside.
In blender or food processor, process cottage cheese until almost smooth.
Add sour cream, eggs, flour, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Process until combined.
Stir in onions and mushrooms.
Pour into greased dish.
Bake about 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: beef cabbage soup
directions: In a large pot, brown beef; drain well.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until carrots are done, about 1 hour.
This freezes well.
It is better the second day.
It makes enough you'll surely want to share.

title: white christmas cookies
directions: Chill combine ingredients overnight.
Roll out dough and cut out cookie shapes.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: raspberry kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Combine gelatin with sugar.
Add gradually to the egg whites, beating to stiff peaks. Make sure sugar is well dissolved by rubbing a bit of the mixture between your fingers.
It should not feel grainy.
Blend in vinegar, then fold in chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoon onto brown paper lined or Teflon lined pans.
Be careful not to use recycled paper bags to line the pans.
Bake 25 minutes in a preheated 250° oven, then turn off oven, but do not remove kisses for another 20 minutes.
The kisses are light and fragile so remove from pans carefully, using spatula or pancake turner.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Put all of it in a bowl and stir it.
Then you put it in the oven for 1 our.
Then you take it out and eat it.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, egg yolks and Cool Whip together; set aside.
Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Put a layer of cake pieces, then the Cool Whip mixture, then the Butterfingers. (Crunch up Butterfingers; beat up while still
in wrapped package.)
Repeat until all the mixtures are gone.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix together cream cheese, vanilla and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed until blended well. Add egg and mix well with mixer. Line muffin tins with foil liners. Place 1 vanilla wafer in each liner. Pour cheese mixture over wafers, filling 3/4 full. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Remove from pan when cool. Chill and top with fruit, preserves, nuts or chocolate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as usual.
Melt butter, then add crushed crackers.
Layer broccoli, cheese and crackers, ending with crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grits casserole
directions: In pan boil water and salt.
Stir in grits.
Reduce heat and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add small amount to eggs; return to pan.
Stir in sausage and 1 cup cheese, milk and butter. Stir until butter melts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until top begins to brown.

title: pickled cantaloupe
directions: Peel and dice cantaloupe.
Soak in 1 cup each of vinegar and sugar overnight.
Remove fruit.
Boil 2 cups each of vinegar and sugar.
Add cantaloupe to syrup and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Pack cantaloupe in jars or put in large bowl.
Boil syrup 10 minutes, until thick.
Pour over cantaloupe and seal in jars or pour over fruit in large bowl.
Cool.

title: plaza iii steak soup
directions: Melt oleo and whip in flour to make smooth paste.
Stir in water.
Saute chuck; drain off grease and add to soup.
Add onion, carrots and celery.
Add frozen vegetables, tomatoes, Accent, beef concentrate and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to a simmer and cook until vegetables are done.

title: blender mayonnaise
directions: Measure oil into a measuring cup.
Place egg, mustard, salt, vinegar and 1/4 cup of the oil into a blender container.
Cover container and blend at low speed.
Immediately uncover and pour remaining oil in a steady stream while blender remains on low speed.
As soon as oil is incorporated, switch to high speed for 5 seconds.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in loaf pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the zucchini and yellow squash, onion and pepper until tender in very little water.
Melt margarine and corn bread stuffing mix.
Put 1/2 in bottom of baking dish, save 1/2 for the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in small saucepan, in small amount of oil.
Brown ground beef in large pot and drain off fat.
Add all ingredients together with beef, except cheese and tortillas. Simmer 50 minutes.
Add tortillas and cook 10 minutes.
Pour into mugs and sprinkle with cheese.

title: scramble
directions: Mix the salad oil, Worcestershire sauce and season salts together well in a bowl and pour over all the other ingredients, which have been mixed together in a large roaster.
Try to distribute the oil mixture over as much of the cereals, etc., as possible.
Bake in a very slow oven (250°) for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring and turning mixture with a wooden spoon every 15 to 20 minutes.
Be careful not to crush cereals.

title: moist 'n easy creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes through the cake with utility fork.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix pecans, eggs, sugar, vanilla, buttermilk and oleo in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook on stove top burner until it's all blended good together and right before it comes to a full boil, take it off the stove.
Pour it into your pie shell and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: plains georgia cheese ring
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put into a mold and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from mold; if a mold with a round empty center is used, put strawberry jam in center.
Serve with crackers.

title: slow-cooked swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Cut steak into serving size pieces; dredge in flour mixture.
In a skillet, brown steak in butter.
Transfer to a slow cooker.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over steak.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients
together in frying pan. Put creamed potatoes on top.
Bake in oven at 375° until set.

title: grandmoo's chocolate roll
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with sugar until lemony and thick. Grease a flat cookie sheet with margarine; line with wax paper.
To yolks, fold in sifted flour and cocoa.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add vanilla and pinch of cream of tartar.
Fold in with egg yolk mixture.
Spread mixture over sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 minutes.
Take out.
Sprinkle towel with confectioners sugar and flip roll onto and over.
Spread roll with whipped cream (whipping cream with vanilla and confectioners sugar; make this the night before) and berries of your choice (raspberries taste the best). Fold up and enjoy!

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Mold in long rolls.
Refrigerate.
Slice when chilled.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 or 10 minutes at 425°.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix and boil rhubarb, sugar, water and pineapple for 20 minutes, then add jello and mix until jello is dissolved.
Pour into small containers and freeze.

title: banana pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, gradually blend milk and pudding mix.
Add egg yolks and 1 teaspoon vanilla, beating with mixer until smooth. Cook, stirring constantly, until pudding comes to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap and cool thoroughly, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream to which remaining vanilla has been added.

title: walnut pie
directions: Add first 4 ingredients until butter melts.
Beat in eggs and rest of ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Put walnuts on top. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until top is firm.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Reduce heat and continue baking for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pumpkin praline cake
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed 1 minute.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Pour half of mixture into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Combine last 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle over batter.
Top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Put oil in frying pan.
Let it get hot.
Cut center out of biscuits.
Slowly drop biscuits in oil and let brown on both sides 5 minutes altogether.
Cool and roll in sugar.

title: chuck wagon casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except biscuits, butter and corn meal.
Place mixture in casserole.
Bake 10 minutes.
Dip biscuits in melted butter, then in corn meal.
Arrange around the casserole, then bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar, flour, cream and vanilla.
Put rhubarb in pie crust.
Pour mixture over rhubarb; dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 3/4 hour.
Cover with meringue made from egg whites.
Brown.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil all ingredients, except noodles and tomatoes, until tender, about 2 hours on low heat. Take chicken out of broth and cool.
Debone chicken.
Tear in small pieces and return to broth.

title: congo squares
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: faye's pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Store in refrigerator overnight, toss and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add 1/2 cup milk and mix well. fold in 1 9oz. carton cool whip.
Pour into crust and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: stuffed cabbage(golabki)
directions: With sharp knife, remove core from cabbage.
Discard wilted leaves. Immerse cabbage in boiling salted water for 5 to 7 minutes, removing leaves as they become tender.
Drain well; cool. Preheat oven to 325°.
Trim main leaf stems.
Fry onion until golden brown.
In a large bowl, combine onion, beef, pork, rice, salt and pepper.
Spread a cabbage leaf flat.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons filling on leaf near base.
Fold bottom of leaf over filling, then sides toward center.
Roll tightly.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Repeat with remaining filling and cabbage leaves. Place golabki in buttered frypan, seam side down.
Cook over medium heat until browned, 8 to 10 minutes, turning once.
Arrange golobki, seam side down, in medium roasting pan.
Combine flour and bouillon in closed container.
Shake well.
Mix with tomato paste.
Pour over golabki.
Cover and bake 40 minutes until tender.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Place buttermilk in shallow bowl.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk; place 2 or 3 pieces at a time in bag.
Shake to coat.
In a large, deep frying pan, place oil and heat at 375°.
Add chicken pieces (do not crowd); cook until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towels before serving.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Salt to taste.
Mix it all together and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or at 375° for a longer time and sprinkle cheese on top after it is done.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, then form into loaf and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then add glaze and bake another 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Let cream cheese and butter soften; blend well and add remaining ingredients. Spread over cool cake.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Mix with salt.
Refrigerate overnight (24 hours) in covered container.
Drain and rinse. Return to container.
Put on sugar and vinegar; stir and let stand 24 hours in covered containers in the refrigerator.
Stir well, put in freezer container and freeze.

title: halibut with vegetable crest
directions: Lay fish in a single layer in a shallow rectangle or oval 1 1/2 to 2 quart baking dish.
Pour lemon juice over.
With a fork, mix together carrot, tomato, green onion, mayonnaise, cream cheese, parsley and pepper.
Add salt to taste.
Mound vegetable mixture equally atop fish.
If made ahead, cover and chill up to overnight.

title: glazed cream cheese puffs
directions: In mixer, cream the cream cheese; then add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Line muffin pans with paper liners and place one wafer in each liner.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over wafers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool, then spoon pie filling over puffs.
Refrigerate.
Makes 24 puffs.

title: panforte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Keeping them separate on a cookie sheet, toast the almonds and hazelnuts for 10 minutes, until lightly browned. Remove from the oven and reduce oven temperature to 300°. Place the hazelnuts in a dry towel and rub to remove the skins. Leave skins on the almonds.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Form into 3 to 4 balls.
Put oil in a frying pan.
Cook meat balls until light brown all over and no longer pink inside (15 minutes).

title: pizza snacks
directions: Place crackers on greased baking sheet.
Spoon pizza sauce over crackers.
Sprinkle cheese over top and place one pepperoni on to each cracker.
Cook at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine and cream together the sugar, brown sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add beaten egg well, then mix in peanut butter. Sift flour and soda into batch and stir.
Form into shape desired on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: mama's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream lard, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well. Combine remainder of ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.

title: lemonade
directions: Into 1-quart jar with tight fitting lid, put sugar and lemon peel; add 1 1/2 cups very hot water.
With lid fitted firmly, shake jar until sugar is dissolved.
Add lemon juice. Refrigerate.

title: jodie's sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, white sugar, 1/4 cup oleo, cinnamon and salt.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Combine crackers and brown sugar; sprinkle on top.
Drizzle with remaining oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Melt oleo.
Add onion and broccoli. Cook together on stove top until almost done.
Add soup, milk, Cheez Whiz and cooked rice.
Turn into greased casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: easy magic muffins
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: butterscotch blonde brownies
directions: Warm oleo just to soften.
Beat in eggs and then sugar.
Add mixture of dry ingredients and finally vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake!
They will rise some and drop.
Remove from oven when "dropped" about halfway to center of pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut while warm.
Store tightly covered.

title: chicken-noodle parmesan(quick main dish - preparation time: about 20 minutes)
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Add noodles and chicken or turkey.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Makes 4 1/2 cups or 4 servings.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: chutney
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt and syrup drained from apples. Bring this to a boil, stirring as you add apples.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add raisins and ginger.
Cook 15 minutes, until thick.
Chill.

title: pineapple wedding punch
directions: Mix well and set aside to chill.
At serving time:
Add 2 quarts ginger ale, chilled.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender.
Pour off half the water.
Add the margarine, salt and pepper.
Mix with electric mixer for 5 minutes. Add milk; mix well.
If too thick, add water to consistency you like.

title: blueberry mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thick. Fold in whipped cream, blueberries and vanilla.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: basic brownies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Process hot butter mixture with chocolate chips until smooth and blended and chocolate pieces have melted, about 15 to 20 seconds.

Add eggs through feed tube while machine is running and process a few seconds longer. Add remaining ingredients and process with 3 or 4 quick on/off turns. Scrape down sides of bowl as necessary. Spread batter evenly in a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Yield:
25 brownies.

title: vanilla bananas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine lemon juice, vanilla and nutmeg.
Roll bananas in mixture, then in cornflakes.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sunny silver pie
directions: Set
gelatine
in cold water to soak.
Place 4 egg yolks in
a bowl.
Add lemon juice and rind of 1/2 lemon and 1/2 cup sugar. Place
in a pan of boiling water, stirring until light, thick
and creamy.
Remove
from
fire, but keep in hot water. Add the gelatine and mix well.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and mix well.
Fold egg whites into cooked
mixture.
Pour
into a baked pie shell.
Place in icebox several hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl beat condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten with fork.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Put the beef cubes, chicken cubes, celery, carrots and cabbage into the 2 cups boiling water.
Combine all the above ingredients; simmer for 2 hours.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease and flour 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Lightly brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain.
Add garlic powder and seasoned salt, chili powder and tomato paste and mix well.
Stir in water.
Gently fold in beans and corn.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the cheese, until well blended. Place in a 2-quart, 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 8 (really 5 or 6).
Very rich but so delicious! Casserole with a salad and bread makes a meal.
Do not cook in the microwave, as it softens water chestnuts.
You can reheat servings in microwave okay.

title: realemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy saucepan, combine 1 1/3 cups of sugar and cornstarch.
Add ReaLemon. In small bowl, beat egg yolks.
Add yolks to the ReaLemon mixture.
Gradually add water, stirring constantly.

title: quick light christmas fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 3 loaf pans or an angel food pan.
In a large bowl, cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Stir in lemon extract and flour mixture. Combine candied fruits and nuts with 1/2 cup flour; add to batter.
Pour into prepared pans.
For loaf pans:
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
For angel food pan:
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium-high heat and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Reserve 1/4 cup cheese for topping.
Stir in remaining cheese until melted.
Add elbows.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: natchez squares
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, flour, lemon rind and juice; mix well.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt
chocolate and butter.
Cool
and
set
side.
Mix milk, sugar, cornstarch, salt and
eggs
and
add to chocolate mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Pour
into two unbaked pie shells. Sprinkle 1 cup coconut and 1 cup
pecans on top of each.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Mix together.
Add onion and pepper (cut these in rings).
Mix vinegar and sugar. Top with pepper and onion rings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix as directed and press into pizza pan; bake. Cool.

title: butterscotch grahams
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Line a 15 x 10-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread mixture over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.
Yields 24 bars.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the onions and garlic in oil.
Add meat; brown over medium heat.
Add tomatoes, water, celery and allspice.
Stir in mushrooms and stir well.
Cook over medium-low heat 1 1/2 hours. One hour after sauce has been simmering, cook the noodles.
Stack noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese (in layers). Bake at 350° until sides are bubbly.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1 cup of flour,
sugar,
salt
and yeast. Combine milk, water and margarine in a
cup
glass measure. Heat in microwave until liquids are
very warm, about 120° to 130°.
Gradually add liquids to
dry
ingredients
and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with
electric
mixer, scraping down sides of bowl occasionally.
Add egg
and
tablespoons flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping
down
sides of bowl occasionally. Remove mixer. Stir in enough
flour to make a stiff dough.

title: brenda's strawberry cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork roast
directions: Brown pork, bone side down at 425° for 30 minutes.
Mix sugar, water, white vinegar and green peppers.
Heat on stove until sugar is dissolved.
Mix cornstarch, water, paprika and parsley flakes. Add to vinegar mixture.
Pour over pork.
Reduce temperature to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: giant spice cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine the cake mix, ginger and baking soda. Stir in water, molasses and vanilla; mix well.
With floured hands, roll into 10 to 12 balls.
Place 3-inches apart on greased baking sheets; flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes or until surface cracks and cookies are firm.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yield: 10 to 12 giant cookies.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Melt the chocolate over hot water.
Add the sugar and 2 cups of the hot milk. Cook until mixture is smooth.
Soak the bread crumbs for 20 minutes in the other 2 cups of hot milk; combine chocolate mixture with crumbs; add the slightly beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 1 hour or until a silver knife inserted comes out clear.

title: ranch cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, white and brown sugar.
Add eggs, unbeaten, and blend.
Stir in corn flakes and oats.
Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Add coconut and vanilla extract.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: brandon's hot mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together the meal, eggs, oil, buttermilk and corn.
Stir in peppers and onion.
Pour half of batter in a greased skillet or pan.
Sprinkle top of batter with half of the Cheddar cheese.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Season yogurt to taste with dressing mix.
Combine ingredients in a plastic or glass container.
Shake well.
Use as a dip with vegetables or over salads as dressing.
Try it with baked potatoes, too!
Makes 2 cups.

title: e-z sticky buns
directions: Place frozen rolls in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pudding and cinnamon.
Melt brown sugar and butter, nuts and/or raisins together.
Pour over rolls.
Cover with wax paper or foil and cloth.
Let rise 8 hours or overnight.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Enjoy!!!!

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Cut tomatoes and onions together and cover with scant 1/2 cup salt, then cover with water.
Cook 10 minutes and drain well.

title: mini swiss tarts
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Mix onion with cheese.
Stir together egg, cream and dry ingredients.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Fill pastry shells 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 48 tarts.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion and pepper in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add spinach mixture.
Combine spinach, onion and pepper with 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella, Ricotta, 1/2 cup Parmesan and egg.
Set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour, milk, cream and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thick.
Set aside.
Spread spinach mixture over a cooked, dried noodle and roll up.
Continue until all mixture is used up.
Spread a small amount of cheese sauce in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Place rolls in dish; pour over remaining sauce and bake 40 to 50 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fast fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan; stir until blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up vegetables in a large bowl. In a medium bowl mix remaining ingredients until creamy. Pour over vegetables and let cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours for cake pan or 1 hour at 350°.
May be cooked in loaf pans.
Adjust time and temperature according to pans.
Don't overcook.
Best banana bread or cake ever.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except water.
Put into a baking dish.
Pour water over top, cover, and bake at 375 degrees until soft, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: marshmallow cookie sandwich
directions: Put a scoop of ice cream in between the two cookies.
Take about 6 mini marshmallows and put them on the sides of the ice cream sandwich.
Skip a spot between the spaces.
The marshmallows will stick on the side of the ice cream.
Then put the chocolate chips in the empty spaces on the side.
Refreeze the sandwich for about 5 minutes, then take it out and enjoy!

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in pineapple and bread.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fat free chocolate cake
directions: Popcorn without using oil.
Season to taste with any of the following items:
chili powder, onion powder, garlic powder, grated Parmesan cheese or cinnamon.
If popcorn is sprayed with non-stick vegetable coating while hot, the seasoning will adhere more easily.

title: skillet barbecued chicken
directions: Place cut up fryer in skillet.
Mix catsup and Coke together. Pour over chicken.
Bring to boil; then cover and reduce heat. Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chicken is tender.

title: marinated pot roast
directions: Place meat in glass or clay container, NOT metal.
Sprinkle garlic salt on both sides of meat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat to marinate.
If meat is frozen, start the night before and let set at room temperature.
If it is thawed, start night before and let set in refrigerator that night and put out at room temperature the next day.

title: pecan stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks with a fork; add next 7 ingredients, mixing well. Spoon pecan mixture into egg white shells.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.

title: pork chops in beer
directions: Brown chops.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Reduce heat; cook, covered, until tender, about 1 hour. Eat and enjoy.

title: roasted romano redskins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash and quarter potatoes.
Place in an extra large mixing bowl.
Drizzle with oil; toss.
Then toss with cheese and seasonings.
Place potatoes into a 9 x 13-inch casserole baking dish.
Bake for approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender and slightly browned.
Serve immediately.
Serves 10.

title: holiday tea punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; pour over ice cubes in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: ashley bars
directions: In a large pot on medium heat, melt and mix peanut butter, corn syrup and sugar.
When melted, mix in and coat Special K. Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool 5 minutes and shape by pressing lightly with spoon into pan.
In a double boiler or in a medium pan on low, melt chips together.
When smooth, spread on top of bars.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Stir until mixed.
Drop on waxed paper with spoon.
Let cool.

title: corn chowder
directions: Steam scallions in water, covered, until wilted.
Add stock, seasonings and potatoes.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Gradually add skim milk, then add corn.
Heat to almost scalding and cook 1 minute.
Put 2 cups of chowder in blender or food processor with skim milk.
Puree.
Return to pot and heat.
Contains 0.7 grams of total fat per serving.

title: purple cow
directions: Blend all together in blender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add rest of ingredients and heat through.

title: lemon meringue pie(no cook filling)
directions: Combine lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Gradually stir into condensed milk.
Add egg yolks (slightly beaten); stir until blended.
Pour into prepared shell.
Put egg whites in small mixer bowl.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat at high speed until stiff, then gradually add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry.
Put on top of pie filling.
Bake in slow oven at 325° until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: mouth watering fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in large, heavy saucepan.
Slowly bring to a rolling boil.
Let this mixture boil for 8 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat and add chocolate chips, marshmallows and butter.
Mix only until the chips and marshmallows are melted. Add vanilla and nuts; blend.
Spread into a large, ungreased pan. Let cool.

title: combico salad
directions: Cut broccoli, cauliflower and celery into bite size pieces. Slice onion.
Mix all vegetables in a large bowl.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Mix onion, hash browns, shredded cheese, sour cream and soup. Place in baking dish.
Top with mixture of cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Dissolve together cornstarch and water.
Add boiling water. Cook until thick and clear; cool.
Beat egg whites until they stand in soft peaks, then beat into cold cornstarch.
Beat until firmer peaks are formed.
Gradually add sugar; beat, beat, beat until firm peaks form.
Add vanilla; beat in.
Put on pie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: the preacher's sunday casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble hamburger over potatoes and add soups.
Add layer of onion, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: creamy chicken corn noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken, noodles and broth until noodles are tender.
Add corn, chicken soup and mushroom soup.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
(Use Kluski noodles for best results.)

title: pretzels
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat egg yolks until lemony.
Work the butter and egg yolks into the flour with hands or a spoon.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roll out; slice and shape as desired.
Brush pretzels with milk and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake on cookie sheets in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes; turn once.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and sugar.
To this add softened butter and egg, then pumpkin.
Using shortening, grease the loaf pan.
Pour batter into the loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together Crisco, eggs and sugar.
Add to flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add bananas last.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: mexican pot roast
directions: Brown meat in a little oil.
Add water, seasonings and vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove cover; cut meat into bite-size pieces and simmer for an additional 30 minutes, until thickened.
Serves 4.

title: chou-fleur aux tomatoes(france)
directions: Boil cauliflower in salted water for 10 to 12 minutes; refresh in cold water.
Drain.
Arrange cauliflower in buttered 10-inch shallow baking dish.
Place tomatoes around edge.
Season with salt, pepper and half of the butter.
Mix crumbs with cheese; spread over vegetables.
Pour remaining butter over all.
Bake for about 30 minutes in a 375° oven or until slightly brown.

title: louie's lemon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breasts on a cookie sheet. Combine lemon juice, oregano and oil.
Baste chicken with lemon mixture.
Cook until chicken is done, approximately 35 minutes. Salt and pepper can be added to taste.
Serves 4.

title: weight watchers chili
directions: Brown meat and add with other ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve with rice or pasta.
Twelve protein and free vegetables for the whole pot.

title: louisiana rolled pork roast
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Line a roasting pan with foil.
In a small food processor or with a mortar and pestle, crush the garlic, paprika, salt, black, white and red peppers, thyme and dry mustard.
Set aside.

title: beef ragout
directions: Put all ingredients, except cornstarch and water, into slow cooker (crock-pot) for six hours or so.
(I cook mine during work hours.)
Bring to a boil just before serving.
Mix cornstarch and water and add to meat mixture.
Boil until thickened.
Delicious served over rice or noodles.

title: fudge candy
directions: Pour into pan greased with butter and cool.
Very good.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, flour, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add coconut.
Pour into well-greased pie pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: hot dog or hamburger bun pie
directions: Open buns and put them face down in baking dish.
Melt butter and pour slowly over buns.
Mix sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla. Pour over the buns.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done. Serve warm or cold.
You can use hot dog buns or hamburger buns. This is like an egg pie.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Set aside.
Saute meat and onion; drain.
Pour in baking dish.
Blend tomatoes and soup.
Put noodles over meat. Pour soup mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook in 400° oven until cheese melts.

title: pear-tuna bake
directions: Cut 4 thin slices off pear and save for garnish. Chop remainder of the pear in a shallow baking dish. Gently combine the pear and tuna. Mix the remaining 5 ingredients and add to the tuna-pear mixture. Stir gently. Top with pear slices. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit medley punch
directions: In blender, puree strawberries.
In container combine strawberries and remaining ingredients except ginger ale.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Before serving, add ginger ale and ice ring.

title: prize buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift
flour.
Add soda and sift again.
Cut in shortening, using
fork, until particles of mixture are the size of a pea. Add
buttermilk
to
make
a
soft
dough.
Knead
until ingredients are well blended.
Roll on floured board.
Cut and bake on baking sheet at 425° until brown.
This makes about 18 biscuits.
When
biscuits are barely brown, they can be cooled and frozen.

title: chow mein candy
directions: In double broiler, melt chips, shortening and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in the noodles and marshmallows and drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: cheese cake
directions: To make crust:
Grease a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Form crust from graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 stick butter. Mix and spread in pan.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar and add egg yolks, one at a time.
Blend thoroughly.
Then add the hot water.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in potatoes and nuts.
Lastly, fold in egg whites, beaten stiff but not dry.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: lemon mousse(norwegian citron dessert)
directions: Dissolve gelatin, but substitute 1 cup lemon juice for 1 cup of water.
Let cool and set slightly.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and fold in sugar.
In third bowl, beat whipping cream.
Stir and fold together egg whites, whipped cream and jello.

title: cornbread confetti salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to directions.
Cool, then crumble.
In large bowl, combine other ingredients.

title: marvettas spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crispy; set aside.
Brown rice and onion in bacon grease.
Add tomatoes and garlic.
Cover and simmer until rice is done.
Cover with cheese and bake until cheese melts. Crumble bacon on top.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and add cocoa.
Mix sugar and eggs together.
Beat by hand, then add cocoa mixture.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick cookie bars
directions: Mix together and press into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Dough will be stiff.
Use a spatula to press the dough out in the pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
(Time may vary, depending on oven.)
Cut in squares.

title: quick chicken and rice soup
directions: Cube chicken.
Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large saucepan until brown.
Add broth, water, vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to low heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 7.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir margarine, sugar and milk to a full boil.
Continue stirring
at rolling boil 5 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour into a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: cranberry stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts until 1/2-inch thick.
Top each breast with 1 tablespoon cranberry sauce.
Turn on sides and roll, enclosing cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle rolls with salt and pepper. Dip rolls in flour, then into eggs and then into coconut mixed with crumbs.
Place rolls in shallow baking pan that has been greased with some of the clarified butter.
Spoon remaining butter over rolls.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cook carrots and zucchini separately until tender but still firm.
Drain and place into a skillet with butter and sugar.
Stir over high heat until vegetables are lightly glazed.
Place chicken on serving platter and surround with vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: guacamole(does not turn brown)
directions: Peel and slice avocados.
In small bowl, combine avocado slices, minced garlic, lime juice and Tabasco; mash with fork until blended.
Add tomato and salt and pepper to taste.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding according to the directions on the box. Combine the sour cream and Cool Whip with the pudding.
Put a small amount of pudding in the bottom of a large serving bowl and layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mix until all ingredients are layered.

title: mom's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Pour 1/2 cup salt over mixture and let soak for 3 hours.
Drain good.
Bring vinegar and spices to boil; add cucumber mixture and heat through.
Do not boil.
Put mixture in hot jars and seal.
Crispy, crunchy, tasty pickles!

title: no waste peach jam
directions: Wash peaches; remove seeds and bad spots.
Quarter peaches and put in food processor.
Remove.
Add 1 cup sugar to 1 cup of peach mixture and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Add Sure-Jell to 4 cups of peach mixture.
Cook 15 minutes at rolling boil.
Seal in hot jars.

title: sour cream cherry pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Stir in cream cheese and cook in top of double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly. Spoon a little of this mixture in with your egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks to mixture and cook 3 minutes or so longer.
Add flavoring and pour into graham cracker pie shell. Top with cherries or any other topping.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix together; chill.
Slice and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: In large bowl, combine the cheeses, eggs and the seasonings until well blended.
Set aside.
Mix cooked meat and spaghetti sauce together.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Cook 1 hour on low heat.

title: funnel cake
directions: In mixing bowl combine eggs and milk.
Sift together baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture; beat smooth.
If thick add milk. If too thin, add flour.
Heat oil to 360°. Pour 1/2 cup batter into funnel or measuring cup.
Release batter into the oil in a swirling pattern.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Turn and cook 1 more minute.
Drain and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes approximately eight 4-inch cakes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies(diabetic)
directions: Into a blender place the egg, juice concentrate, applesauce, raisins and vanilla.
Blend to break up raisins.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Ina bowl mix oatmeal, flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Blend in raisin mixture with the margarine.
Mix well.
Drop batter by rounded tablepoonsfuls onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool on rack.
Store in airtight container or freeze if you wish.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Hull strawberries.
Slice 3 berries; set aside.
In covered blender container at medium speed, blend whole berries and remaining ingredients until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
Serve soup in chilled soup bowls or cups, garnished with reserved sliced strawberries.

title: apricot baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in casserole.
Combine sauce.
Spread half over chicken.
Cover with wax paper or paper towel.
Microwave on Full power for 6 to 7 minutes.
Turn pieces over, add remaining sauce. Cook 6 to 7 minutes.
Allow to stand 5 to 6 minutes.
Can bake at 350° in regular oven for 1 hour.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.
Use for beef or chicken.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In skillet, brown chicken, garlic and onions in Crisco.
Add rice to this with 1 1/2 to 2 cups of water.
Cover until rice is tender.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in small balls; press small nuts on top and push down.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Put 2 cups sugar, water, salt and pecans in saucepan; bring to boil.
Brown 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet and let it melt to a light caramel color.
Pour this into first mixture.
(Be careful as this could cause a splash.) Continue to cook until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Add butter and stir until it cools and thickens a bit.
Quickly drop by spoonful on wax paper which is on newspaper.
When cool, pralines will lift off.

title: sugar-free jello mold
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Combine gelatin and boiling water in an electric blender. Cover and blend at low speed until dissolved, 1 minute.
Add measured liquid, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Cover and blend on high speed (15 seconds).
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into a large jello mold. Chill until firm.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Soften cheese and mix all ingredients, reserving 1 cup pecans.
Shape into 1 large ball or 2 small balls or into a log shape and roll in the reserved pecans.
Chill. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: shrimp scampi(serves 2)
directions: Pat shrimp dry on paper towel and set aside.
In a wide frying pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in onion, oil, garlic, lemon juice and salt.
Cook until bubbly.
Add shrimp to pan and cook until shrimp turns pink (about 5 minutes).
Blend in parsley, lemon peel and hot pepper seasoning.
Turn into serving dish.

title: amish pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Cook in frying pan or on griddle until puffy and bubbly, turning to brown the other side. Very light and fluffy.

title: chicken ball
directions: Beat first three ingredients.
Blend in next 2 plus 2 teaspoons parsley.
Refrigerate.
Shape into ball and chill for 4 hours (covered).
Roll in nuts and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in peaches and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Stir together flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and milk.
Cut through shortening with fork until dough forms a ball.
Drop mixture by 6 to 8 spoonfuls onto hot fruit.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with cream or whipped cream if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and margarine.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in a bowl.
Fold in and mix well. Place corn flakes on bottom of pastry crust.
Spoon in rhubarb mixture atop the corn flakes.
Bake at 350° until bottom of pastry shell browns.

title: baklava
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 12 x 18-inch baking pan. Mix nuts, zwieback, cinnamon and sugar.
Place 5 sheets of phyllo in pan; brush with butter.
Sprinkle on nut mixture.
Place 3 sheets and repeat process until the entire package of phyllo has been used.
Cut halfway through in depth in diagonal lines.
Pour remaining butter on top.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all marinade ingredients and pour over mushrooms. Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: egg souffle
directions: Brown meat; drain on paper towels.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir in crumbled bread, meat and cheese.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beans and pasta
directions: Saute onion in olive oil.
Add carrot, beans, water, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Bring to boil;
add pasta.
Add liquid if necessary;
simmer 5 minutes.
Add basil, simmer 5 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Combine pineapple and eggs.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Pour into a greased baking dish. Toss bread cubes in melted butter.
Place on top of pineapple. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: sour cream peach dessert cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix vigorously and scrape sides with spatula.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven. Can top with whipped cream or use ice cream.

title: swiss mocha coffee
directions: Combine and store in airtight container.
To serve, add mixture to hot water by teaspoon to taste.

title: east west stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry beef until cooked.
Set aside.
Pour oil into wok. Add onion, celery, carrot, green beans, turnip and mushrooms. Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Pour in broth and reduce heat.
Cover and steam for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in honey, soy sauce and dissolved cornstarch.
Return meat to wok.
Place spinach on top of meat and vegetables.
Cover and steam for 1 minute.
Uncover and stir.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Combine and place bacon over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: smothered meat balls
directions: Beat egg; add bread crumbs or crackers.
Stir in soup mix; add beef.
Wet hands and shape meat into balls.
Brown on all sides in Dutch oven.
Add sliced onion, cream of mushroom soup and about 2 inches of water.
Bake in 400° oven for 50 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: vegetable cutlets
directions: Mix vegetables and parsley.
Beat eggs and add to vegetables. Add salt.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Stir in matzo meal and let stand 30 minutes (we didn't let stand).
Form into patties and fry in vegetable oil until golden brown on both sides.
(We add 1 1/4 cups grated zucchini and another egg.)

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine all ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple-broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli and unpeeled, cored apple into bite-sizes.
Add raisins, nuts and sliced onion.
Toss.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour this over first ingredients and mix.
Chill before serving.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls in jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix Miracle Whip, cream cheese and Hidden Valley dressing.
Spread mixture on cooled crescent rolls.
Top with finely chopped vegies and top with cheese.

title: orange and coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs in, one at a time.
Add coconut.
Bake in a 9-inch pie shell at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until set in middle.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Coat with flour. Fry in oil.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in 1/3 of dry ingredients.
Beat in 1/2 of milk.
Add another 1/3 dry ingredients, then milk and end up with dry mixture.
Beat well. Add vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Make 4 layers or cupcakes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Add milk, lemon juice and vanilla; spread on crust.
Mix strawberry juice with cornstarch and cook over low heat until thick.
Cool.
Add strawberries and pour over cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; add onion and garlic salt.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Great on spareribs!

title: burger supreme
directions: Cook hamburger until done and crumbly. Mix eggs, cheeses, tomato sauce, garlic salt, Italian seasoning, black pepper, salt and cooked hamburger.
Place bread slices on baking sheet and cover slices with mixture.	Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes or until cheese is partially melted and sandwiches are heated. Garnish with olive slices.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, butter and syrup until a smooth blend.
Add flour, salt and eggs together; beat slightly.
Then add vanilla and pecans.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell for 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Slice celery and carrots.
Microwave on High until a bit soft.
Layer with water chestnuts, broccoli or peas (whatever). Add cream of chicken soup.
Sprinkle blanched almonds on top and bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, mushrooms and green olives.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put in large baking dish.
Spread sour cream over this.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over sour cream.
Spread crescent rolls over top.
Brush with melted margarine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken, remove from bone and dice.
Mix with vegetables, celery soup and chicken soup.
For crust mix 1 1/2 stick melted margarine, 1 1/2 cup milk, 1 1/2 cup self rising flour in a bowl. Mix well and pour over top.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: apple cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake in muffin pans at 375° until done.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in iron skillet.
In a small bowl, put chili powder, salt and sugar.
Add 1/2 cup of water to make paste.
Fry paste in hot oil.
Immediately add remaining water to skillet.
Bring to a boil; then simmer.
Dip corn tortillas in sauce until tender.
Fill with cheese and onions.
Roll.
Stack in a long pan; alternate with cheese and onion.
Pour sauce over top. Cover with foil and heat in a hot 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: In a
small saucepan, heat pineapple until hot and stir in jello
until it is completely dissolved.
Pour into a large bowl. Let cool.
Add cottage cheese and chill until partially congealed. Prepare Dream Whip.
Fold prepared Dream Whip into jello mixture; stir in pecans.
Pour into 2-quart dish.
Chill until firm.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Cook beans according to package directions; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese and cracker crumbs, mixing well.
Pour mixture into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onions, green peppers, celery and garlic.
Saute until onions are transparent.
Add green onions with 1 cup of bread crumbs.
Mix in 1 cup of water or crab juice (pour juice from can of crabmeat, then add water to make 1 cup).
Beat eggs; add crabmeat.
Melt 1/4 to 1/2 pound of butter or margarine in casserole.
Dish in all of the above ingredients.
Add 2 to 3 bay leaves.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, parsley and paprika.
Drizzle some melted butter (or margarine) over top.
Heat in oven at 400° to 450° for 30 to 45 minutes, until hot throughout. Remove bay leaves.

title: quick and easy donuts
directions: Heat cooking oil in skillet.
Separate refrigerated biscuits. Poke hole through center with index finger.
Drop into hot oil; fry until golden brown on each side.
Drain donuts on sheet of newspaper.
Roll fried donuts in the mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Children eat them as fast as you finish.

title: good smooth play dough(yields 1 serving)
directions: Place all ingredients, stems, seeds and all into a blender or food processor and make into a paste.
Freeze in ice cube tray and use as necessary.

title: southern shrimp and chicken
directions: Cook bacon.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Brown chicken in batches over high heat, transfer to bowl.
Add flour to pan.
Cook until browned.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic; cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in broth, salt, pepper and thyme.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Return chicken to pan; cook 5 minutes more.
Stir in shrimp and cook about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add salt, yolk of one egg, then flour. Add vanilla.
Chill and work into balls. Press with thumb and fill with tart jelly (plum or apricot).
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes on ungreased pan.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Combine ingredients. Blend in blender. Refrigerate. This is equal to a regular-size can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: elegant potatoes au gratin
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cool.
Peel and shred on medium grater.
Shred cheese.
Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of potatoes and cheese in casserole.
Sprinkle with salt. Pour unwhipped cream over potatoes and cheese layers.
Top with bread crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
This can be prepared night before or frozen.
Allow time to return to room temperature or bake extra time.

title: potted plant
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and stir together until smooth. Add pudding and milk.
Stir until thickened, then add Cool Whip. Set aside.
Crush Oreo cookies.

title: yum yum coffee cake
directions: Topping:
Mix together brown sugar, white sugar and cinnamon. May add chopped nuts. Set aside.

title: white trash
directions: Melt the margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips together.
Mix Rice Chex, raisins and peanuts in a large container.
Coat with melted ingredients.
Pour into large paper bag with 10x sugar.
Shake well.

title: stuffed cabbage soup
directions: Combine ingredients and cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: cherry or apple dump cake(low-fat)
directions: In the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole, dump pineapple and pie filling.
Mix the fruits together.
On top, dump lite cake mix.

title: john's easy cookie recipe
directions: Remove lid of cookie jar.
Insert hand into jar.
Grab cookie. Remove hand from jar.
Eat cookie.
Repeat instructions.

title: uncle john's pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together and fry on hot griddle. Thin and full bodied.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour over ham.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken stew
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on low heat 8 to 10 hours. Discard bay leaf before serving. Serve each with a 2-inch square of cornbread or make cornbread sticks.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring the first four ingredients to a boil at 100% power.
As soon as it boils, boil 2 minutes more.
Add baking soda and mix well.
Will make mixture foamy.

title: souperior meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: lazy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in oven for 1 hour at 300°.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Mix together and pour dressing over.
Toss.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown meat; drain and put in crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on low for 1 hour.
Makes about 1 gallon. Serve with nacho chips or crackers.

title: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack. Cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding and pineapple, juice included.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Blend in whipped topping.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix instant pudding with undrained pineapple.
Whip cream. Fold in pineapple mixture.
Cut cake into 3 layers.
Fill with mixture.
Frost top and sides.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Saute chicken, onion and garlic in margarine until chicken is lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch; cook 1 minute longer.
Add broth, carrot, lemon juice, peas and salt; boil 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve with lemon wedges. Serves 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolk slightly.
Add milk and dry mixtures alternately to egg yolk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Use double boiler.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and margarine.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in pie shell. Top with Cool Whip or meringue.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix above ingredients.
Roll into 1 inch balls and freeze.
Bake at 350 for 10 minutes.

title: korean short ribs
directions: Place ribs in one layer in shallow pan.
In medium bowl combine soy sauce, oil, scallions, garlic, salt (if using), pepper, honey and sesame seed.
Mix well and pour over ribs. Cover with plastic wrap and let marinate in refrigerator overnight.
The next day refresh marinade with a little water; some will have been absorbed by the meat.
Broil at least 8 inches from coals for about 30 minutes or until well browned on all sides. Turn frequently to prevent burning.
May be cooked in oven broiler as far as possible from heat element.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Beat one egg in at a time.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: beef with broccoli(chinese)
directions: Cut beef steak across grain into thin 1/4-inch slices.
Mix sliced beef with soy sauce, cornstarch, sherry, sugar and Accent and set aside.
Cut broccoli into flowerets, peel stalk and cut into slices.
Pour 2 tablespoons oil into a hot wok/skillet; add salt and broccoli.
Stir and turn constantly until broccoli turns dark green.
Remove from wok and spread on plate.
Put remaining 3 tablespoons oil in wok.
Add ginger or onion slices.
Stir in beef mixture and keep turning constantly until almost done.
Add cooked broccoli to beef.
Mix thoroughly until beef cooked to desire degree of doneness.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: meat loaf piquant
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in baking dish, then put this piquant sauce over the top.

title: chicken divine
directions: Layer broccoli, then chicken, then mixture of soups, mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice and cheese.
Top with more grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: norwegian chocolate cake
directions: Melt the margarine and chocolate.
Cool.
Whip the eggs and sugar thoroughly.
Mix the chocolate, eggs and flour carefully. Pour into greased spring-form pan and bake in lower part of oven at 425° for 14 minutes.

title: fancy beans
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Brown meat and onions.
Combine all ingredients in a covered casserole dish.
Bake until warm.

title: royal ice cream cake
directions: Line sides and	bottom	of
a loaf pan with ladyfingers that have been
split.
Place
alternate layers of vanilla ice cream and the ladyfingers to top of pan.	Cover the entire top with layer of
crushed
vanilla	wafers.
Put in freezer overnight.

title: pie plant torte
directions: In pie plate make crust.
Over crust spread rhubarb, flour and sugar; mix.
Beat together eggs, cream, flour and salt.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 375° until custard is almost set.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tsp. cinnamon.
Sprinkle over pie.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, water chestnuts, pecans, grapes, celery and ginger.
Blend mayonnaise, vinegar, soy sauce, onion and curry powder.
Toss dressing with chicken mixture.
Chill.

title: shake pickles
directions: Fill gallon jar with sliced cucumbers.
Cover with 1 cup pickling salt and water. Shake each day for 4 days.
Drain and rinse 3 times (do not remove cucumbers from jar).
Mix 2 tablespoons alum with enough water to cover cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Shake every hour or two.
Rinse 3 times and cover with pure vinegar.
Let stand 10 days.
Drain vinegar off.
Discard vinegar.
Add 2 tablespoons pickling spice (put spice in a bag) and 3 cups sugar.
Shake to mix.
Next 3 days, add 1 cup sugar and shake.
Leave in gallon jar or put into smaller jars.

title: individual lime cheesecakes
directions: Line 12 muffin pans with paper baking liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each.
Place cottage cheese in blender or food processor. Cover and process until smooth.
Combine Neufchatel and cottage cheese in medium bowl, beat on medium speed until smooth and creamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, lime rind, lime juice and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spoon mixture over wafers.

title: cool tuna salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, cucumbers, onions (chopped), egg whites and dill weed.
Chill.

title: fettuccine with bacon and red peppers
directions: Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion, bacon and garlic; cook until onion is tender and bacon is cooked, stirring occasionally about 8 minutes.
Stir in peppers, peas and broth; simmer 1 minute.
Transfer mixture to large bowl. Add pasta and toss well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve, passing grated Parmesan separately.
Serves 4.

title: peanut oatmeal cookies
directions: Put in a bowl and mix together.
Drop spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, melted butter, eggs and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls in 9 or 10-inch pie dish. Beat egg and add 1/4 cup cheese. Place in bottom of pie shell. Brown meat; drain. Add other ingredients; simmer 10 minutes and put in pie pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Put remainder of cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.

title: brownies
directions: Mix chocolate and butter in saucepan, stirring to blend. Cool.
Add sugar and mix well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Blend together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add egg yolks, milk and margarine.
Blend all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Using a wire whip to blend, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vanilla and pour into a 10-inch pie crust. Cool and top with meringue, Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: baked turkey
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter over low heat.
Add the flour and stir until well blended.
Cook one minute.
Slowly add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Let sauce cool; add chopped chicken, egg yolk, salt and celery salt.
Form into twelve small cones.
Mix bread crumbs with ground sage.
Roll cones in crumbs.
Beat egg; add water.
Dip each cone in egg and roll again in crumbs.
Place on a greased baking pan and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings. Carbohydrate 11 g, protein 16 g, fat 16 g, calories 253.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix water, rice, consomme, soup and butter.
Place in a casserole dish.
Place pork chops on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until pork chops are done.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients in two quart bottle.
Use bubble wands, hanger; blow through straws which have been dipped in container and pulled out.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into small pieces.
Chop onions and mix with cheese and mayonnaise.
Let set at least 3 hours.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Peel and cut in bowl.
Mix in enough mayonnaise to moisten the potatoes.
Add desired amount of cut-up Velveeta.
Put some on top; season to taste.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 1/2 hour, depending on size of dish used.

title: candy bar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder, and soda together, add to butter and egg mixture alternatley with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and candy bars which have been melted in double boiler. Pour batter in a greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Mix and spread in greased pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: russian black bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl combine 3 cups of the all-purpose flour, 1 cup of the rye flour, the whole bran cereal, the yeast, coffee crystals, caraway seed, sugar, fennel seed and 1 tablespoon salt. In a saucepan heat together the 2 1/2 cups water (3 cups if using bread flour), molasses, butter or margarine, chocolate and vinegar just until warm (115° to 120°) and chocolate and butter are almost melted; stir constantly.
Add molasses mixture to flour mixture in mixer bowl.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in remaining 3 cups rye flour and as much of the remaining all-purpose flour as you can mix in with a spoon.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Place all peppers, vinegar, sugar and coloring in a cooking vessel.
Bring to full boil.
Strain and add pectin to the jelly. Let stand 10 minutes or until beginning to jell.
Pour into sterile jars and cover with paraffin.
Serve on a block of cream cheese with crackers.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and remove eyes from potatoes.
Thinly slice.
Cook onion in butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and cheese. Heat to boil, 1 minute.
Put potatoes in ungreased pan.
Pour on cheese sauce.
Cook, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Sprinkle on bread crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: millionaire candy
directions: In a Dutch oven pan over medium heat, combine sugar, margarine, Pet milk and vanilla. Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in Hershey's Kisses until dissolved.
Then stir in Marshmallow Creme until dissolved.
Stir in nuts and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
(Be sure to have someone available to help with stirring and dropping onto wax paper.)

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 35 to 45 minutes).

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and milk in saucepan on stove, stirring until melted. Remove from stove and stir in nuts. On buttered wax paper, drop by teaspoonfuls. Chill in freezer to set (about 10 minutes). In microwave safe bowl, melt almond bark in microwave for
1 1/2 minutes.
Let cool a bit; stir well. Dip caramel/nut mixture in chocolate. Put on waxed paper to harden. Put back in freezer for about 10 minutes. Store in airtight container.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix water, soups and rice together and set aside.
Grease casserole dish and place chicken in.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: tennessee pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a regular loaf pan. On wax paper, sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. In medium bowl, cream shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add the eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Stir in pumpkin, then dry ingredients in 4 additions alternately with water, until smooth. Do not overbeat. Fold in the nuts. Pour into prepared pan and bake 45 to 55 minutes or until cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean. Turn onto wire rack; turn right side up to cool.

title: apple betty
directions: Arrange apple slices in greased 8-inch round dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice.
Combine oats, sugar, cinnamon and nuts; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add nuts; mix.
Crumble mixture over apple slices.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: mini blintzes
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar. Let cool.
Combine egg yolks, cream cheese (at room temperature) and 1/4 cup sugar until smooth.

title: oven stew
directions: Pour 1 package Lipton onion soup mix over all.
Cover casserole with heavy foil, then lid, to seal.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours or bake at 350° for 3 hours (I found 5 hours is best).
Do not open to look in while baking!

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil in frying pan.
Remove and arrange chicken in casserole.
Combine soup and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yummy apple cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Dutch apple dessert and eggs.
Add diced apples and stir by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix a topping of butterscotch chips, walnuts and sugar and sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: no egg raisin cake
directions: Bring to a good boil the first 5 ingredients; then cool.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: whatever casserole
directions: Cook elbow macaroni until al dente.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients with macaroni and place into a 2-quart casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs, if desired.
Cover.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes until hot.
Feeds 6.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Marinate chicken legs 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Soften butter and Crisco together; mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients to butter mixture.
Mix thoroughly until batter is smooth.
Pour into a large Bundt pan which is greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan on stove.
Sprinkle brown sugar on bottom of pan.
Peel and thinly slice apples, then arrange in one layer over brown sugar.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on package and pour over apples. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Let cool.
To serve, cut and then flip slice over and top with Cool Whip.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil.
Blend well, then beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Turn into greased and floured 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then prick cake with 2 tined fork or skewer completely through to bottom of cake.

title: party rye canapes
directions: Mix together cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Spread on bread and broil until light brown and serve.

title: potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add potatoes and onions.
Toss to coat well.
Cover.
Chill 4 hours. If desired, sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Makes about 4 cups. Recipe may be doubled.

title: blanche's corn souffle
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk and beat well.
