Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat.
Add cans of corn and stir with a spoon; do not beat.
Melt butter and add to mixture; stir.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 1 hour).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk; mix well. Spoon into a 2-quart casserole. Cover with topping. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked mushroom rib-eye steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup and water. Add red pepper, garlic and milk into bowl and stir until smooth.
Sprinkle steaks with salt, black pepper and red pepper.
Put steaks on baking pan and spread mushroom mixture and sliced mushrooms over the top.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until meat is done.
This is good with mashed potatoes.

title: lemon pie
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch pan, freeze milk (30 minutes).
In a 9-inch pie plate, mix crumbs and butter.
Press to bottom and sides.
In a large bowl, mix well with beater milk, until stiff.
Slowly mix in lemonade and sugar.
Pour in crumb crust.
Freeze.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Cream together cheese and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Line small muffin tins with paper liners. Add small amount crumbs to each liner.
Fill 2/3 full with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Let tarts remain in oven 20 minutes.

title: mushroom soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion and mushrooms and brown until tender.
Stir in flour, using a fork to prevent lumps.
Slowly add broth and milk, stirring constantly. Add bay leaves.
Simmer on low heat until thickened.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serves 4; 367 calories per serving.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.

title: sinfully rich nonfat fudge sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch; stir in evaporated milk.
Cook over low heat for 3 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring constantly with whisk.
Continue cooking 1 to 2 minutes longer or until sauce is thickened and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or cold with fresh fruit, cake or nonfat frozen yogurt. Cover and refrigerate leftover sauce.
Yield:
Approximately 7 servings.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mini cheesecake tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together in a large bowl.
Line mini muffin tin with mini muffin liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each liner; place spoonful of mixture over wafer (3/4 full).
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan when cool.
Chill; top with fruit.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook cauliflower as directed on package.
Drain.
Mash well. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Beat oleo, sugar and Crisco until creamy.
Add flour, milk, vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Beat 5 minutes or more.
Spread on cake.

title: little smokies roll-ups
directions: Cut bacon into three sections.
Wrap each sausage in a bacon section.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Cover with brown sugar and bake until bacon is done at 350°.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in the lukewarm water, flour, salt and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Let stand, uncovered, at room temperature 3 to 4
days.
Stir 3 times daily. Cover at night.
Using starter is simple, but always remember to keep back at least 1 cup of starter for the pot.
This you feed with 1/2 cup water, 1/2 cup flour and 1 teaspoon sugar. Let stand until bubbly and well fermented for at least a day before using.
Store in refrigerator.
If the starter is not used within 10 days, add another teaspoon of sugar.

title: hot rice
directions: Prepare rice according to directions; set aside. Saute the onion in butter. Add hot peppers to taste.
Add tomatoes; mix well. Add to rice. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tater soup
directions: Boil the potatoes in as little water as possible and boil down.
Add carrots and onion and finish cooking. Add butter, celery soup and milk. Bring to a boil. Add Velveeta cheese and simmer until time to serve.

title: butter orange fluff
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add brown sugar gradually, beating to a light, fluffy mass.
Stir in orange rind. Serve on pancakes or waffles instead of syrup.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all together and let set.
Use the gelatin dry.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Stir in eggs until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
In skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Using 2 teaspoons of mixture for each round, cook about 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Mix together next three ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add butter.
Pour in pie crust and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: date bread
directions: Mix together nuts, dates, baking soda and salt.
Set aside. Pour boiling water in a bowl with shortening.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Mix with first mixture; add eggs, vanilla, sugar and flour.
Pour mixture in a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 5-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Lightly toss first 4 ingredients together in bowl.
Fry bacon until brown.
Stir sugar, salt, pepper and dry mustard into vinegar and water.
Add to beaten eggs and mix well.
Pour egg mixture into hot bacon and fat and stir until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Pour over potato mixture and toss lightly. Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble cornbread; melt margarine and mix along with poultry seasoning and pepper.
Divide in three parts.
Mix both soups and broth well.
Line bottom of casserole dish with 1/3 of crumbs. Spread 1/2 of chicken over crumbs.
Pour 1/2 of soup and broth mix over this.
Repeat this with
another layer of crumbs, chicken and soup.
Sprinkle top with remaining crumbs.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream margarine or butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, salt, soda and oatmeal and add to first mixture; mix well.
Press half mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan; pack well.
Spread raspberry preserves.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: charla's wild rice with sausage(makes 6 to 8 large portions)
directions: Slice sausage.
Dice all onions and bell pepper.
Drain mushrooms.
Cook margarine, onions and bell pepper in a skillet until tender.
Add garlic powder, parsley, salt, black pepper and sausage.
Cover and simmer, about 20 minutes or until sausage is done.

title: mary's chili
directions: Brown sausage, beef, onion and green pepper in skillet. Drain.
Put in crock-pot on low with all other ingredients.
Cook 5 to 6 hours.

title: tangy yogurt dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: grandma's mexican dip
directions: Mix and heat at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with taco chips. (May be microwaved.)

title: lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles according to package directions.
In skillet, combine sausage, onion and garlic; cook until brown.
Stir occasionally; drain.
Stir in next 7 ingredients; bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
In medium bowl, blend Ricotta, egg, parsley and salt.
Spread thin layer of sauce in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer 1/3 each lasagna, remaining sauce, Ricotta mixture, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 375° oven until bubbly for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add salt, sugar, butter, flour and corn syrup.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into unbaked crust and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
If crust begins to get too brown, turn heat down to 300° after 15 minutes.

title: fudge brownies(low-fat - special diet)
directions: Coat 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable spray and set aside.
Combine all ingredients except flour and pecans.
Spread batter in pan.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or spring to touch.
Cool on rack.
Yields 16.

title: better-than-sex cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium saucepan, combine pineapple with its own juice and sugar; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until thick and syrupy, approximately 20 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven and pierce top with a fork at 1-inch intervals.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake. Cool immediately.

title: mexican chocolate
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Cover and puree until bits are dissolved.
Serve hot.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, beans, 1 cup picante sauce, onion, garlic, bread crumbs, eggs, cumin and salt; mix well.
Put into ungreased pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Pour off drippings. Combine remaining picante sauce and brown sugar.
Mix well. Spread on top of meat loaf.
Cook another 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together; set aside.
Dissolve 1 package yeast in 1/2 cup warm water, then add the Wesson oil and buttermilk.
Mix and add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Keep covered in the refrigerator until used.
Only take out amount as needed for biscuits.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Do not let biscuits rise before baking.
Bake in a 450° oven for 12 minutes.

title: festive fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to boil.
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Stir in marshmallows until melted.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate chips next.
Stir in chopped nuts and vanilla. Spread in a buttered 8-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut in pieces.
Makes about 30 pieces.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour batter in and bake for 15 minutes.

title: rice lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, combine rice, 1 egg and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
In another bowl, combine 1 egg, Mozzarella, Ricotta, 1/3 Parmesan and parsley.
In a large skillet, brown beef, stirring to break into bits.
Add sauce and oregano.
Heat.
Evenly spread hot rice mixture into an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with half the cheese mixture and meat mixture.
Repeat layers. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hash browns
directions: In bowl, mix together Cheddar cheese, cream of chicken soup and sour cream. Pour over potatoes in pan. Cook 30 minutes in oven preheated to 375° or until center is bubbling. Remove from oven and add crushed corn flakes (about 1 cup). Pour 1/2 cup oleo or 1 stick, melted, on top of corn flakes. Return to oven and continue to bake until brown.

title: nut bars
directions: Put 1/2 jar of peanuts on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt Eagle Brand milk, marshmallow cream and peanut butter chips; pour over peanuts.
Top with the rest of the peanuts.
Press, cut and serve.

title: ricotta cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, then add eggs.
Beat well.
Then add cheese and extract, then beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 14 minutes.
These can be topped with canned vanilla icing or cream cheese icing.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt the margarine.
Add the sugar and crushed pretzels.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, then mix with hamburger.
Put in casserole dish; bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Chinese noodles.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar and drop by spoonfuls in deep hot oil.
Drain on paper towels and dust with powdered sugar.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients in order listed except the last 2.
Place in greased pan.
Mix crackers and margarine; sprinkle on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine the cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken in margarine.
Dredge in cracker crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan (spray with Pam). Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crawfish etouffee(lacour style)
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add crawfish tails and crawfish fat.
On low heat, cook about 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and green onion tops.
Simmer a few minutes, until seasonings blend.
Serve over rice.

title: quick quiche
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
In blender, combine eggs, milk, butter, Bisquick mix, salt and pepper.
Blend for a few minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese, bacon or ham, onions and herbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean; cool.
Allow 10 minutes before cutting.

title: fruit flan
directions: Any kind of fruit can be used except fresh pineapple (peaches, grapes, etc.).

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (8 to 10 minutes).
Remove and cool.
Mix together thoroughly cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch mix.
Spread on crust.
Top with veggies.
Cut into small pizza wedges.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until creamy; add egg and molasses and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to molasses mixture alternately with boiling water.
Beat after each addition.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Mix eggs with lard, then add other ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out onto flour covered wax paper.
Shape into cake size and lay in greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Make 4 to 5 layers.
Then add dried apples or fried apples to each layer.
You can also make Christmas cookies out of this recipe.

title: apple topped pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and transfer to baking dish.
Cover pork chops with onion, apples and raisins.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except whipping cream.
Whip the cream and stir in.
Pour into crumb crust or prebaked pie crust.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, salt, water and corn syrup in top of double boiler, mixing thoroughly.
Place over rapidly boiling water.
Beat constantly with electric mixer at high speed.
Cook 7 minutes or until the frosting will stand up in peaks.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: "hot fudge sauce"
directions: Heat cocoa and sugar until very hot, melting sugar and cocoa. Add butter; mix thoroughly.
Add milk; stir constantly.
Let milk boil for one minute, then add vanilla.
Stir.

title: icebox cake
directions: Prepare chocolate and vanilla pudding as directed on package in separate pots.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, place whole graham crackers on bottom, totally covering it.
Pour half of chocolate pudding on top.
Layer whole crackers on top of pudding and then pour vanilla pudding on top.
Layer graham crackers on top again and finish with rest of chocolate pudding on top.
Crush a few crackers and crumble it on top of last layer of chocolate pudding.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Keep chilled.

title: cream turkey and pasta primavera
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, prepare rigati according to package directions; add broccoli, carrot, green onions and red pepper the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In the same saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Add rigati pasta-vegetable mixture and turkey (or chicken).
Over low heat, heat through, stirring often.
Makes 5 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
25 minutes.

title: frozen, rhubarb strawberry jam
directions: Strip and cut rhubarb in pieces.
Stir together rhubarb and sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, stir to dissolve sugar, bring to a rolling boil; boil 5 minutes, stir constantly. Add jello; stir and bring to a boil again.
Pour into scalded jelly jars; fill to 1/2 inch from top for expansion and freeze. Makes 1 quart.

title: antipasto
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
Serve with large crackers.
Can be kept refrigerated several days.
Will serve "lots" of people.

title: classic philly cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325° (300° if using dark nonstick spring-form pan). Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter; press firmly onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake for 10 minutes. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, flour and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add sour cream; mix well. Add eggs 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended. Pour over crust. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until center is almost set. Loosen cake from side of pan; cool before removing rim of pan. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cut corn off cob and scrape cob.
In a saucepan, add corn, water, milk, bacon drippings, salt and pepper.
Bring slowly to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook for 10 minutes or until tender. Stir occasionally.
Mix flour and water until smooth.
Stir into corn.
Cook 1 minute or until thickened.
Add margarine.
Serves 6.

title: layer fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, then jam.
Alternately add flour, sifted with allspice, and buttermilk in which the baking soda has been beaten smooth and dissolved.
Last add nuts, raisins and coconut.
Mix well.
Place in two greased layer pans.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: deep dish cherry pie
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Melt butter in that dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour on top of melted margarine (do not stir with margarine).
Pour pie filling over flour mixture.
Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blue cheese spread
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until dissolved.
Beat together the Blue cheese, Cheddar cheese and sour cream; stir in gelatin mixture.
Pour into a 3-cup mold; cover and chill until firm. Unmold onto serving plate.
Serve on fancy assorted crackers. Makes about 2 1/2 cups spread.

title: e-z yeast bread
directions: Mix together 1 cup flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a bowl. Heat until warm (120° to 130°) the milk, water and oil.
Remove from heat. Slowly add egg to warm mixture. Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Beat until blended.
Scrape bowl and then beat 300 strokes.
Add remaining flour and stir until it is ready to be worked with hands.
Punch down. Form into loaf.
Place in greased pan.
If you like, brush with egg and sprinkle with seed.
Let rise again until doubled in bulk. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden and tap on the loaf makes a hollow sound. Remove from pan and cool, if you can wait.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, flour, salt and powdered sugar.
Pat into pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix eggs, lemon juice, flour and sugar; beat.
Pour on top at once.
Bake 25 minutes more. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Place in food processor with steel blade and pulse.
Then blend until uniform in texture.
Add pecans.

title: beer dip
directions: Melt Cheez Whiz slightly in microwave and mix in softened cream cheese.
Add garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce; add beer last.
Let stand overnight.
Pour into hollowed out pumpernickel bread.
Use remaining pieces of hollowed bread for dipping.

title: fried rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add scrambled eggs with the cooked rice.
Sprinkle with soy sauce and gravy sauce.
Mix thoroughly and cook for about 5 minutes.
Add chopped green onions and tops.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Slice across tomatoes to make not too thick, not too thin.
Season and coat with meal.
Fry in hot oil in pan 1 layer at a time.
Turn over when brown and transfer when done with spatula to a plate with paper towel to drain on.
Repeat until all are cooked.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill for 2 1/2 hours. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and cool slightly.
Beat egg yolks and add to chips.
Whip egg whites.
Add sugar slowly. Whip cream.
Fold in whites.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Tear angel food cake into walnut-sized pieces.
Put layer of cake and layer of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do in 2 layers.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: fried apples
directions: Melt butter in a skillet. Peel, core and slice apples and place in the skillet. Cook over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the sugar and cinnamon. Cover the skillet tightly and cook over low to medium-low heat, continuing to stir occasionally, until the apples are soft. Remove the lid and simmer so the liquid will somewhat evaporate and become more saucy.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana coffee cake
directions: Cream well the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and bananas. Add, sifted together, the flour and soda.
Add milk and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and spread with topping of melted margarine, brown sugar, coconut or raisins and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute rice and onion in butter until transparent.
Place rice mixture and mushrooms in a deep-sided 3-quart casserole dish. Bring liquids to a boil and add to casserole.
Cover tightly with foil.
Cook for 50 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until lightly browned.
Parboil eggplant in salt water until tender.
Add bread crumbs and cream of mushroom soup.
Fold in eggplant.
Shred grated cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple chicken stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first six ingredients; set aside.
In a large skillet or wok, stir-fry chicken in oil for 5 to 6 minutes or until juices run clear.
Add the vegetables; stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in pineapple and reserved soy sauce mixture; heat through.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: raspberry glazed chicken drummettes
directions: In medium bowl, combine salt, pepper, jam, mustard, garlic and vinegar; whisk until mixed.
Place chicken in a large plastic food storage bag.
Add jam mixture.
Seal bag; turn to coat chicken with mixture.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight. Spray baking dish with cooking spray.
Cook chicken at 350° for 50 minutes.
Transfer to platter; sprinkle with scallions.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Whip sour cream and cream cheese together.
Spread on bottom of shallow casserole dish.

title: christmas egg nog
directions: Beat 1/4 cup sugar into egg yolks; stir in milk.
Slowly cook over hot water until mixture coats spoon, stirring constantly. Chill.
Add salt to egg whites and beat stiff.
While beating, add remaining 1/4 cup sugar gradually.
Fold in egg whites.
Whip the cream into the mixture separately.
Add vanilla.
Chill several hours.
Serve with nutmeg.

title: valentine special cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, food coloring, cocoa, salt, buttermilk, flour and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Mix vinegar and soda.
Fold into first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in two (9-inch) cake pans.

title: no knead crescent rolls
directions: Use a large bowl to mix in.
Combine shortening and boiling water or milk; stir until melted.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Stir, then add cold water.
Put both packages of yeast in lukewarm water and dissolve thoroughly.
Combine all 3 mixtures in large bowl; stir well.
Will be a little wet. Cover and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Shape into small balls for rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: silly pudy
directions: Mix together and let stand for a couple of hours.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, add mayonnaise.
Cool.
Add celery, onions and corned beef; whisk and stir (8 x 8-inch pan).
When jelled, spread sour cream on top.
Parsley on top.
Serves 8 or 9.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil fryer.
Allow to cool and remove meat from bone.
Melt butter in 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Add stuffing mix.
Place chicken on top.
Pour soups and broth over chicken and stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: three layer jello
directions: Bake 10 minutes at 350.
Must cool before middle layer is put on top.

title: twenty minute cake
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar and flour and set aside.
Bring to a boil margarine, salad oil, water and 1 package liquid chocolate.
Add liquid mixture to flour and sugar.
Add eggs, salt, sour milk and baking soda.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, start frosting.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add salt.
Mix chicken broth, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Add to skillet.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Add chicken and vegetables and heat through.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.
Sprinkle with noodles and additional soy sauce, if desired.

title: peanut fudge
directions: Bring sugar and evaporated milk to a boil in saucepan.
Boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips, vanilla, margarine and peanuts.
Beat until thickened and creamy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Cut into squares.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator. May substitute peanut butter chips for chocolate chips.
Yield: 80 servings.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Cream butter; beat in sugar, potatoes, milk and cocoa.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.

title: cow patties
directions: In a double boiler over simmering water, melt the chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth.
Remove from the heat; stir in raisins and peanuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Remove from heat. Add chicken, soup, sour cream and half of the grated cheese. Soften tortillas in microwave for approximately 1 minute on High; cut into fourths.
Place a layer of tortillas in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, then a layer of sauce mixture.
Continue to layer, ending with sauce.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: congealed fruit salad
directions: Heat water to boiling and remove from heat.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add fruit and stir again.
Place in a bowl or Pyrex dish and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin casserole
directions: Mix the above ingredients together.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in pan or dish you plan to bake the casserole in.
Pour the mixture into dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon on top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until set and browned.

title: german potato salad
directions: Add onion to nearly crisp bacon and cook until transparent. Add vinegar, sugar, flour, water, salt, pepper and celery salt. Keep cooking and stirring until it is bubbly gravy; add water to keep it a thin consistency.
Pour over diced potatoes and eggs. Serve warm.
Makes 2 casseroles full.

title: green chili pasta dip
directions: Chop onions and tomatoes; mix with green chiles and black olives.
Add vinegar and oil; mix well.
Chill while boiling pasta.
Cool pasta under cold running water.
Mix with other ingredients.
Serve.

title: mama's escalloped mac 'n cheese with ham
directions: Cook macaroni by directions to al dente and drain.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan. Add flour. Cook and stir 1 minute. Add milk, whisking rapidly. Simmer 1 minute.
Add Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper. Set aside.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon margarine in large skillet and cook mushrooms and onion until wilted. Add ham and cook 2 minutes. Add cheese sauce, cayenne pepper and cream. Cook 1 minute more.
Pour into macaroni and mix well.
Pour into 10-cup casserole dish and sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Place under broiler on high until golden brown (2 to 3 minutes).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: registry resort's brownies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter until light and fluffy. Add corn syrup.
Mix and scrape down the sides of the bowl.
Add melted chocolate; mix well.
Scrape down the sides of the bowl again.
Gradually add eggs, mixing well.
Stir the remaining ingredients together; stir into the batter, mixing only until ingredients are incorporated.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 18 brownies.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine muffin mix and cheese (prepare muffin mix according to directions).
In a saucepan, stir together remaining ingredients and heat.
Spoon muffin mixture into greased 2-quart casserole dish, then spoon soup mixture over muffin mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden.
Garnish with additional cheese, green onions and sliced cherry tomatoes, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, sugar and egg.
Then add flour and baking soda mixture.
Make into small balls and press with floured fork on dry cookie sheet.
If needed, blend about 1/2 teaspoon of water into mixture before making balls. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
To test if done, wooden toothpick or straw should come out of cookie clean and dry when stuck in. Always preheat oven for 10 minutes with door closed.

title: fast peach cobbler
directions: Combine margarine, peaches and 1 cup sugar; boil until slightly darker than natural.
Meanwhile, combine milk, vanilla, flour and 1/2 cup sugar in a mixing bowl; pour this batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then pour boiled peach mixture on top of batter. Bake until top browns at 400°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain juice from beets; add water to make 1 cup.
Add vinegar, sugar and cinnamon; bring to a boil.
Pour over beets.
Marinate several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Part of the liquid may be poured off when served.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: raisin pie
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain. Add other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: sparkling pineapple punch
directions: Heat sugar, water and cinnamon to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or until chilled.
Remove cinnamon from syrup.
Just before serving, mix syrup with the remaining ingredients in a punch bowl.
Makes 26 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: cornmeal gravy
directions: Fry meat to have enough grease to cover cornmeal.
Add cornmeal and salt to taste.
Brown meal in grease.
Add milk; stir and let boil until thick.
Serve over any bread.

title: banana fritters
directions: Mash bananas.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Add nutmeg and salt to flour, then add to mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil and fry.
Drain.
Sprinkle with lime juice and granulated sugar.

title: gramma ray's pumpkin cake
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs, sugar and oil until fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done; let stand 10 minutes.
Ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: all-american casserole
directions: Combine rice, beef, egg, onion, salt, parsley flakes, marjoram and pepper. Add 1/2 cup tomato juice; mix lightly. Shape mixture into 18 balls. Place in skillet. Add sugar to remaining tomato juice and pour over meatballs in skillet. Bring to boiling point.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs well.
Add the vegetable oil, zucchini, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Then add the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortenings and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mix.
Stir in oats, rice cereal and coconut.
Form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake in moderate oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: mary's chocolate pie
directions: Melt in double boiler the chocolate squares and butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add one egg at a time and beat separately for 3 minutes each.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: beef bourbon
directions: Heat skillet over medium flame.
Add butter and round steak. Saute until brown.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over steak. Bake, covered, 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: rice dressing casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Saute celery and onions in butter.
While rice is still hot, add grated cheese and mix until cheese melts.
Add the sauteed celery and onions.
Add mushrooms.

title: karen's tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, macaroni, cucumbers, celery and onion.
Mix Italian dressing, Miracle Whip, mustard and pepper.
Pour over tuna and macaroni mixture.
Toss gently.
Chill.
Add tomatoes, dill and sliced eggs before serving.

title: 5 bean hot dish
directions: Drain a little juice of each can.
I put this all in my large crock-pot and turn it on low all morning.

title: vegetable pastry
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Flatten the rolls out on edged cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Spread cream cheese mix over crust.
Top with vegetables.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Bake pork roast wrapped in foil for 3 to 3 1/2 hours at 350° or until done.
Let cool slightly.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Break
roast
into
pieces
and
lay in pan. Pour enough barbecue
sauce over roast to completely moisten. Seal pan
with foil and return to oven for 1 hour at 250°.
You may want to stir it after 1/2 hour.

title: four o'clock tea scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk to egg and then add to flour mixture, gradually adding more milk if necessary.
Knead lightly on a floured board.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into wedges and place on greased baking sheet. Brush with butter and sugar on top.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 15 (4-inch) scones.

title: wild elderberry pie
directions: Mix berries, sugar, salt, tapioca and lemon flavoring.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into pastry-lined 9-inch pan and cover with top crust.
Cut vents in top crust.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking until fruit bubbles through air vents and crust is lightly browned.

title: beer cabbage slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and pepper.
Add celery seed, onion, salt and pepper.
Thin mayonnaise with beer; add to cabbage.
Toss thoroughly; chill in refrigerator before serving.
Excellent with ham or corned beef.
Serves 6.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Grate the cabbage, carrots, onion and green bell pepper and mix together.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce mixture over the cabbage mixture.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly with mixer.
Place on plate and shape into a ball.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Top with chopped nuts (optional).

title: tea biscuits
directions: Mix and cook in small muffin pans at 400° to 425° for about 10 minutes.

title: roasted chicken with fresh herbs and blackberries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash and dry chicken; set aside.
In a food processor, combine butter, herbs, lemon and lime zest, minced garlic, blackberry jam, lime juice, mustard, honey and soy sauce; blend well and set aside.
Sprinkle chicken cavity with juice of 1 lemon.
Place whole garlic cloves inside.
Brush chicken with blackberry-herb mixture.
Roast, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and continue cooking, basting chicken frequently with pan juices.
Cook for 20 minutes per pound of chicken.
Serve on a platter surrounded with fresh blackberries and sprigs of herbs.
Pan juices may be served with chicken, if desired.

title: cashew yam casserole
directions: Beat until fluffy, adding more juice if mixture is dry.
Add cashews to 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Heat in a small frying pan until toasted.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or 35 minutes if refrigerated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn and bacon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray twelve 2 1/4-inch muffin cups with nonstick spray.
In a large bowl, combine flour and salt. Add bacon bits and stir to combine.
In medium bowl, combine milk, corn, eggs, and margarine.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir just until combined.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Pat beef in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer soup, cheese and tater tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
DO NOT SALT!

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix onion soup, beef broth and water.
Heat to blend.
Pour over brisket.
Cook 2 to 3 hours at 350°.
Baste occasionally.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until thickened.
Add milk, cream, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly; chill.
Pour in freezer.
Makes enough for 4 quart freezer.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuits in sugar mixture.
Place biscuits into a bundt pan.
Melt butter.
Mix butter and Karo into sugar mixture.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 20 minutes at 350.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: tunnel of fudge
directions: Cream shortening in large bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add sugar and continue creaming at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours before removing from pan.
Cool completely. Very good.

title: super sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars.
Blend well.
Add eggs and vanilla (lemon extract if desired).
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Stir into butter and egg mixture. Chill dough if necessary.
Shape into small balls.
Roll each ball in sugar then flatten on a cookie sheet with a flat bottomed glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for about 12 minutes.
Dough may also be used in a cookie press.
You can use colored sugar to coat the balls for the holidays.

title: meatballs in creamy paprika sauce
directions: Mix together the turkey, oat bran, ketchup, pepper and garlic. Shape into small balls.
Fry in a nonstick pan sprayed with Pam. Remove the balls when browned.

title: mary lou's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl with an electric mixer until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar, gradually, beating until mixture is thick, smooth and creamy.
Add all other ingredients, then your choice of flavor variation, in the order listed.
Do not cook! Pour mixture into freezer, leaving 2 to 3 inches at top for expansion.
Freeze as stated on ice cream maker.

title: blackberry juice
directions: Put berries in large kettle. Add water to almost the level of the berries. Cook to a boil for 15-20 minutes. Strain to get the seeds out.

title: hamburger potato dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Add tomato soup; mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Have mashed potatoes cooled with one egg beaten in them (can use leftover mashed potatoes).
Put large dips of potatoes over hamburger and bake until potatoes are brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together pistachio pudding and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.

title: scrumptious peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together well your soda and flour.
Cream butter and peanut butter in a medium sized mixing bowl; beat in one ingredient at a time, the granulated sugar, the brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Then add flour mixture, mixing it well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate pieces. Drop from a teaspoon heaped full onto a cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until they are light brown which takes about 10 minutes.
Let cookies cool a minute before removing them with a spatula.

title: homemade brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat until done; drain juices and save.
Debone hens; grind meats in food chopper.
In bottom of a 16-quart cooker, put butter and ketchup.
Add meat, salt and pepper; stir constantly so it won't stick.
Place bread in meat stock; let it soak, then add it to the meat mixture and heat well.
Add corn; stir well.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Melt over hot water and spread on cooled bars.

title: west virginia peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter; beat well.
Add sugar; beat well.
Beat in Cool Whip; mix well.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate.

title: suzie's szechwan chicken
directions: Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce in medium bowl. Add chicken and stir to coat; set aside.
Combine 2 tablespoons soy sauce, sherry, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Set aside. Heat oil in wok.
Add red pepper and cook until blackened.
Add chicken and cook 2 minutes.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add scallions and ginger.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Return chicken to wok; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add soy sauce mixture and stir 1 minute.
Add peanuts.
Serve over rice.

title: crisco cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco well.
Add well beaten eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour and milk, a little at a time.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
